title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs and margarine together and form into crust in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, margarine and eggs together for at least 15 minutes.
Smooth mixture over crust.
Cut bananas lengthwise and place on mixture.
Drain pineapple and pour over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip, nuts and cherries.
Chill.
When firm, cut into squares and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil and drain broccoli; place in greased casserole dish. Blend soup with mayonnaise; add lemon juice and mix.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with grated cheese, then bread crumbs (or crushed potato chips).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: chewy fudge brownies
directions: Blend ingredients well; batter will be stiff.
Add pecan pieces.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° in glass oblong dish greased on bottom with nonstick cooking spray or vegetable shortening.
Do not overbake.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Cut into squares.
Cover tightly after cooling to keep.

title: sunday treat
directions: Mix vinegar, honey, cloves and cinnamon in saucepan.
Heat to a simmer.
Add peach halves; cool.
Chill several hours or overnight; drain.
Serve fruit with some of the liquid over it.

title: ham and broccoli
directions: Cook rice; drain.
Cook broccoli.
Pour rice in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer broccoli on top of rice.
Mix rest of ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Cover broccoli with mayonnaise mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Prepare crumb topping by combining flour, brown sugar and shortening in bowl until mixture resembles course meal. In another bowl, dissolve soda in boiling water. Add molasses and corn syrup; blend well. Pour into unbaked pie shell and sprinkle crumbs evenly over the top. Bake in the middle of the oven for 10 minutes. Reduce heat and continue to bake for 35 minutes or until filling is set. Do not overbake!

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut and rinse in cold water.
Drain again and add 1 cup sugar.
Let set overnight.
Add celery, pimiento, onion, wine vinegar, oil and green pepper.
Mix and marinate 24 hours. Delicious salad; no sauerkraut taste, just good!

title: creamy macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as per box; drain.
Combine with next 4 ingredients.
Spoon into greased pan.
Top with crushed crackers. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning together; set aside. Layer in order: bean dip, guacamole, sour cream mixture, picante sauce, chopped tomatoes, and sliced black olives.
Cover with cheddar cheese and top with jalapenos to taste.
Refrigerate.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together potatoes, onion, soup, sour cream and butter. Top with corn flake crumbs and, if desired, pieces of butter here and there on top of corn flake crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer bean dip in bottom of a pie plate.
Spread sour cream on top.
Spread taco sauce on top.
Sprinkle with cheese, tomato and onion.
Serve with taco chips.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Shred cabbage and place in bottom of dish.
Peel and slice potatoes and put on top of cabbage.
Slice onion and place a layer on top of potatoes.
Crumble corned beef on top and pour soup over casserole.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Combine Carnation with sugar in heavy saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Stir until marshmallows are melted. Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.

title: veggie casserole
directions: *Such as broccoli, cauliflower, whole carrots and water chestnuts (a must).

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: Put cherry pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Put margarine slices on top of cake mix.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Melt sherbet in jello.
Add drained fruit and nuts.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; chill until set.
Garnish with whipped cream cheese.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and save broth for stuffing.
Debone chicken. Cook chopped onion and celery in butter until tender.
Mix 1/2 cup water with can chicken soup.
Add onion and celery to soup mixture and heat.
Mix stuffing according to recipe on package.
Spread chicken on bottom of casserole or pan.
Spread soup mixture over chicken.
Cover chicken and soup with prepared stuffing.
Bake about 1 hour at 325°.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Pierce pie shell.
Beat egg yolk with water and brush shell. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Saute sausage and onion, then stir in flour. Beat eggs with milk.
Set aside.
Sprinkle half the cheese on shell.
Top with sausage, then rest of cheese.
Pour in egg mixture. Sprinkle with parsley. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: hummus
directions: Put all ingredients except salt and paprika in a blender or food processor and puree.
Season with salt.
Garnish with paprika.
Serve with pita bread.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole pan.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add oatmeal.
Mix in Wheaties or Total with your hands.
(The batter becomes very dry.)
Add coconut if you wish.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and cocoa in double boiler. Pour enough milk to mix.
Add egg yolks.
Stir in rest of milk and cook until mixture is thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla. Pour in pie shell. Top with meringue, if desired.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook, rinse and drain pasta according to directions.
Cook mushrooms and pepper in a small amount of boiling water in a large covered saucepan about 3 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Drain well.
Stir together flour and 1/2 cup cold water in a small bowl.
Stir into vegetable mixture in saucepan.
Stir in milk and bouillon.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in the pasta, turkey or chicken and sherry or water.
Spray a 2-quart square baking dish with nonstick spray coating.
Pour the pasta mixture into the dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven for about 10 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pizza hors d'oeuvres
directions: Crumble sausage and brown with onion, bell pepper and celery. Add cheese.
Spread on small slices of wheat bread.
Bake until bubbly.

title: the world's best french onion soup
directions: Heat oven to 400°. On stove top, heat butter in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add onions and stir often until softened and golden brown, about 35 minutes. Increase heat to high and pour in 1/2 broth, stirring until most of the broth has evaporated and onions are browning again. Continue until you have used up 2 cups of the broth. Wrap bay leaf, parsley and thyme in cheesecloth. Add to soup; reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, 15 minutes. Season with Madeira and salt and pepper to taste. Toast bread in oven on a cookie sheet 5 minutes. Divide the soup among 8 ovenproof bowls. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of cheese over each, then top with bread and 2 tablespoons more cheese. Place bowls on cookie sheet and bake until the cheese bubbles, 10 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: country or cured ham
directions: Use a 15 gallon pot.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cok on medium heat for 10 minutes.

title: vienna bread
directions: Combine lukewarm water, sugar and yeast in bowl.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Add salt and oil; mix.
Gradually add flour.
Mix well. Knead until smooth on floured board.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until doubled.
Punch down and let rise again.
Cut into 3 pieces.
Let rise again (15 minutes).
Shape into long loaves and place on greased cookie sheets sprinkled with cornmeal.
Cover with towel and let rise in warm place until doubled.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken-corn soup
directions: Cover chicken with water and cook until tender.
Remove from water; cool.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Set aside.

title: rice salad from france
directions: Mix well in a large bowl.
For the dressing, make an oil and vinegar dressing and add salt, pepper, about a teaspoon Dijon mustard, parsley and basil.
Mix to taste and pour over salad. Serve chilled.
This is authentic, straight from Paris!

title: sour cream fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: apple crumb cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
In large bowl, cream butter and 2 cups of sugar.
When fluffy, add eggs.
Stir dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Beat flour mixture in cream mixture.
Alternate with sour cream.
Beat in vanilla. Stir apples and remaining sugar; fold in batter.
Spoon 1/2 batter into pan.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together, then add bananas. Bake at 350°.

title: chocolate candy bar pie(serves 15 to 20; 9-inch pie)
directions: In microwave, heat candy bars, marshmallows and milk on High 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir after 2 minutes.
Chill 30 minutes until thickened.
Stir occasionally.
Whip whipping cream.
Fold whipped cream into cooled chocolate mixture.
Lightly pour into prepared crumb pie shell.
Freeze until firm.
Cut with wet knife.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Mix jello, cornstarch, Sugar Twin, water and salt in saucepan. Bring to boil, stirring at all times.
Cook until clear.
Cool for about 5 minutes and pour over strawberries that have been arranged in baked pie crust.
Refrigerate for about 3 hours. Serve with Cool Whip Lite.

title: baptist pie (makes 2-9-inch pies)
directions: Mix all ingredients except crusts.
Pour into 2 pie crusts and chill.
Top with additional Cool Whip.

title: best cake ever
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chocolate chips and German chocolate; beat 2 minutes.
Grate chocolate; mix into cake batter.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; chop stems.
Combine in 1-quart casserole, stems, onion and margarine.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Stir in bread crumbs, cheese and seasonings; mound in caps.
Microwave 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Rotate 2 times while cooking. Heat thoroughly.

title: german delight
directions: Heat all but 3 squares chocolate with 1/4 cup milk over low heat.
Beat in cream cheese and remaining milk.
Gently stir in whipped topping until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Melt remaining chocolate, drizzle over pie.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: angel amanda biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in yeast and buttermilk. Roll and cut.
Bake at 450°.
Will keep in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs; add bananas, milk, flour and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice-a-roni
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni as per box instructions.
Place in a 9 x 12 or 9 x 13 baking dish.
Lay chicken breasts on top of Rice-A-Roni.
Season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Cover and bake for 1 hour or until chicken is done in 350° oven.
You may remove cover last 20 minutes or so.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Make your noodle dough.
Roll it out.
Make stuffing out of chopped meat, onions, salt, pepper, eggs, parsley and spinach. Cover half of noodle layer with stuffing, then put second half on it.
Take wooden board and press quarters by using edge of board, but do softly so stuffing moves and forms pillows (each about 6 x 6 cm) and the two noodles layers meet and glue.
Then separate pillows from one another with a knife and cook in a broth for 15 minutes.
Serve it in broth or with potato salad and green salad.

title: orange coconut balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers to fine crumbs.
Add sugar, margarine, orange juice and nuts.
Mix well.
Form into balls and roll each ball in flaked coconut.
Yield: 6 dozen.

title: aunt fanny's cabin baked squash
directions: Wash and cut up squash. Boil until tender. Drain thoroughly. Then mash. Add all ingredients, except 1/2 of the margarine. Melt remaining margarine. Pour mixture in baking dish, then spread melted margarine over top and sprinkle with cracker meal or bread crumbs. Bake in 375° oven approximately 1 hour or until brown on top and set.

title: angel food cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add egg.
Mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add.
Stir in flavoring and coconut. Shape into small balls; roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on a greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: rookie cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix cake mix, eggs, water and shortening.
Mix in pecans.
Shape dough into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll balls in powdered sugar.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: vegetable casserole(feeds 10 to 12 people)
directions: Cook vegetables.
Heat soups.
Layer vegetables in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Pour soup over vegetables.
Add chestnuts, then onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: Heat oil about 1 minute.
Add vegetables with wooden spoon. Stir constantly until food is only wilted, but still crunchy.
The secret of good stir-fry is not to overcook.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Add potatoes, eggs, onion, celery and pickles.
Mix lightly.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rosemary pork chops
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Add oil to skillet.
Add chops and brown well on both sides.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Add shallots, vermouth and rosemary.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with brown rice and carrots.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Bring to boil chocolate, Crisco and milk.
When cool, add sugar, eggs, flour, baking soda and vanilla.
Do not overmix. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix together well, adding eggs, one at a time.
Pour into three 8-inch cake pans (grease bottoms only).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool on rack for at least 5 minutes.

title: big mac special sauce
directions: Blend all the ingredients with a fork.
Keep tightly covered and refrigerated.
Use within a month.
Makes 2 cups.

title: mom's italian cinnamon cookies(pinwheels)
directions: Make a well in the flour and baking powder.
Add eggs, liquid, vanilla and lemon extract.
Beat with fork, bringing in the dry ingredients.
Add more flour to obtain soft, firm consistency.
Rest dough 10 minutes and roll out, using flour to prevent sticking.
After rolling to about 1/4-inch, spread butter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon lavishly.
Roll up.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Lay flat on cookie pan and bake only until lightly golden.

title: coffee-caramel ice cream pie
directions: Spread melted chocolate over bottom of crust. Freeze until set, about 5 minutes. Spoon ice cream into crust; smooth top. Freeze until very firm, about 4 hours. Can be prepared up to 4 days ahead.

title: health nut spread
directions: Mix all and adjust to taste.
Can add more or less of any item.
Serve on crackers, bagels or English muffins.

title: stuffed burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Combine evaporated milk and meat; divide into 5 patties.
On wax paper, pat each to 6-inch circle. Put 1/4 cup stuffing in center of each; draw meat over stuffing and seal.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients, pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Combine cooked rice and cooked broccoli with onion which has been sauteed in margarine.
Add soup, water and Cheez Whiz.
Cook in shallow baking dish at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle grated Colby cheese on top and bake approximately 5 more minutes, until cheese is bubbly.

title: clear lemon filling(used between layers of cake.  terrific!)
directions: Add gradually, stirring.
Spread over or between layers.

title: cream of squash soup(a wonderful way to use up yellow squash. serves 12.)
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter until translucent. Add carrots, potatoes, squash and chicken stock and cook until vegetables are tender, about 45 minutes. Remove from heat. When cool enough to handle, puree in blender, about 1 cup at a time. Return to pot. Add cream and heat thoroughly. Add salt and cayenne if desired. At serving time, sprinkle a bowl with paprika. Can be served hot or cold. Can be doubled.

title: pepper dish
directions: Use electric fryer or frying pan.
Fry cut-up green peppers until soft.
Add onions; fry until soft.
Add hamburger; cook until browned.
Open tomato soup cans; do not add water.
Add soup to pan mix and you have an easy one-dish meal.

title: tex-mex chops
directions: In large skillet over medium-high heat, brown chops in oil on one side, about 2 minutes; turn chops and add salsa and chiles to skillet.
Lower heat; cover and simmer gently for 8 to 10 minutes. Uncover; top each chop with one tablespoon of cheese.
Cover and simmer just until cheese melts.
Serves four.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix sugar and cranberries well!
Set 4 hours; drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Serve!

title: pineapple dump
directions: Open both cans of pineapple and pour juice and pineapple in cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Put dry cake mix on top of pineapple (do not combine).
Melt stick of margarine in saucepan and pour as mix as possible.
Preheat oven at 450°. Bake until cake mix on top is brown (golden brown).
Approximate cost:

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with whipped cream or ice cream and serve.
Double recipe for a 10 x 13 x 3-inch cake.

title: hamburger delight
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Add garlic salt, salt, sugar, pepper and tomatoes.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Drain and put in Pyrex dish.
Add meat sauce with cream cheese and sour cream.
Add grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sausage and potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Spray 13 x 9 inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine potatoes, onions, carrots, oil and soup mix in large bowl.
Stir until evenly coated.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs. Then add vanilla, cinnamon, and baking powder. Divide dough in half. Chill for 3 hours. Roll out and cut. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: robert e. lee cookies
directions: Melt the butter; add molasses, sugar and eggs.
Beat well. Sift together and add to the mixture the flour, soda, cinnamon, ginger and cloves.
Freeze dough for several hours.
Break off pieces of dough (heaping teaspoon-size) and roll into small balls. Roll balls in sugar.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet about 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake in a preheated 385° oven until firm and brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: lipton soup canapes
directions: Cut bread into thirds; remove crust.
Melt
oleo
with soup. Dip bread on both sides in mixture.
Bake at 375° approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Watch carefully.

title: kristy's mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion until done.
Line pan with chips (15 x 11-inch pan).
Add layer of meat mixture, cover with tomatoes and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: cookie cutter cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs and extract. Beat in dry ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters. Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes. Frost with orange flavored frosting.
Better the second day.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Melt butter and chocolate squares over low heat until melted. Remove from heat.
Beat flour, sugar, salt, vanilla and eggs with mixer.
Stir in nuts and chocolate mix.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Heat chocolate chips and milk until smooth.
Remove baking pan from oven and arrange marshmallows on top.
Bake 5 minutes.
Remove and flatten.
Drizzle melted chips over marshmallows.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Cut when cold. Keep in refrigerator.

title: six-can casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 2-quart casserole for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: potato salad
directions: Add all ingredients together except the milk and heat to boil (low heat) until thick.
After mixture is cooled, add canned milk to mixture and stir until your liking of thickness.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Crush enough of the strawberries to get 1 cup.
Add sugar and tapioca.
Cook over medium heat until clear and thickened.
Add butter, cool, stirring occasionally.
Arrange remaining strawberries in pie shell. Pour berry mixture over strawberry halves.
Let cool.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cheese appetizer
directions: Heat all the ingredients and mix well.
Spread on crackers or party rye bread.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan. Combine sugar and milk in pan. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture boils. Cook to soft ball stage (234°). Remove from heat. Quickly add Creme, peanut butter, chocolate chips and vanilla. Stir just until blended. Pour into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Score 1 inch squares while warm. Cut when firm.

title: roast leg of lamb
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Wipe leg of lamb with all natural paper towels.
Place fat side up in a roasting pan.
Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon of salt.
Roast, uncovered, until lamb reaches desired doneness, about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Remove roast to serving platter.
Slowly drizzle 1/4 cup of the Madeira over the lamb. Let stand 15 minutes before carving the roast.

title: quick and easy skillet supper
directions: Slice smoked sausage and brown in large skillet.
Meanwhile, cut cabbage in chunks and steam.
Boil noodles and melt margarine. Combine everything in skillet and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, for a few minutes.
Salt and pepper as desired.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread into small pieces.
Melt butter and add all ingredients; stir well.
Put into greased casserole dish and bake at 350° until brown, about 30 to 35 minutes.
Placing pan in a large pan of water.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook, cool, peel and grate (or chop) potatoes.
Melt 1/4 cup butter and stir in onions; cook onions until tender.
Add cream, soup and 1 cup of Cheddar cheese to butter and onions.
Heat until warm.
Mix potatoes and cream mixture.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: jiffy s'mores
directions: Spread peanut butter on one cracker.
Top with chocolate. Spread marshmallow cream on remaining cracker. Place crackers together.

title: chicken bake
directions: Combine all 3 soups
with onion, mushrooms, parsley and raw rice until well blended.
Spray
a
x
9-inch pan with Pam. Place rice mixture
in
pan;
top
with chicken breasts. (Be sure to remove all
fat from chicken.) Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: fresh lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Use wire whisk.
Blend in cold water, then lemon juice until smooth.
Add beaten egg yolks. Blend thoroughly.
Add butter and boiling water, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil until thickened.
Pour into pie crust.
Add meringue.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: beef stew in the oven
directions: In a
5-quart Dutch oven, layer stew beef and alternate vegetables, 1/3
stew,
1/3 celery, 1/3 peas, salt and pepper. (Easy on the
salt,
the soup has a lot.) Repeat for 3 layers. Cover top with
mushroom soup and 1/2 can of water.
Cover and bake for 5 hours in oven at 225°.

title: jelly roll
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg until thick.
Add sugar (a tablespoon at a time).
Blend in vanilla.
Mix to dry mixture.
Spread batter in 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan, greased and lined with wax paper.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Turn warm cake on towel.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Trim edges off.
Spread with jelly; roll up.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then pour into pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip and chill for 2 hours, then serve.

title: refrigerator cake
directions: Place over heat and stir until marshmallows melt.
Let cool and add orange juice and whipping cream.
Pour this mixture over sliced angel food cake.
(This will cover two medium-size cakes.) Place in refrigerator until firm (about an hour).
Put the evaporated milk in the freezer about 2 hours before you whip it. Shake it occasionally or until it is a frozen mush, and it will whip beautifully.

title: one-skillet breakfast
directions: Chop
bacon
into small pieces and fry in skillet until almost crisp;
drain excess grease.
Add hash browns;
reduce heat
to medium-low.
Continue cooking until browned, turning frequently with spatula.

title: hot chicken or turkey salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 9-inch pan or casserole dish.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Let potatoes thaw.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in large
baking
dish.
Top with parsley.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked broccoli casserole
directions: Layer broccoli, soup, mushrooms and onion rings twice.
Top with cheese and bread cubes.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: wintry day bean soup
directions: Rinse beans.
Place in large kettle.
Cover with water.
Add salt and soak overnight.
Drain.
Add 2-quarts water and ham or sausage.
Simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add onion, garlic, chili powder, tomatoes and lemon juice.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Add salt and pepper, if desired.
Makes 2-quarts.

title: cookie sheet chocolate cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour.
In saucepan, bring to a boil shortening, water and cocoa.
Pour over flour mixture while hot. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Bake in large cookie sheet with sides (greased and floured).
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
While cake is baking, make frosting.

title: martin's catfish
directions: Split whole catfish.
Mix corn meal, black pepper, seasoning salt, garlic powder and paprika.
Fill saucepan with corn meal mixture (1/2-inch thickness).
Butter catfish in mixture and cook in preheated oil at 375° (medium).

title: bambinoes(party snack)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place Ritz crackers in orderly fashion on cookie sheet.
Put one slice pepperoni on top of each cracker and cover with Mozzarella cheese (about 6 to 7 shreds per cracker). Bake for 7 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted on top.
Enjoy!

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in their jackets with bay leaf in boiling salt water until barely tender.
Cool, peel and grate.
Add butter to soup; stir until smooth.
Blend in sour cream, salt, pepper, green onions and cheese.
Pour over potatoes.
Stir gently until blended.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Saute ground chuck, bacon and onion; drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash the potatoes; pat dry.
Prick each potato with a fork in a few places.
Bake potatoes on a rack at 400° for about 1 hour, or until potatoes are done.
Cut a thin slice from top of each potato. Scoop out the pulp into a bowl.
Mash the potato pulp with the hot milk or half and half until fluffy.
Beat in the butter and the green onion.
Add seasonings.
Fry the bacon until crisp; crumble and add to potato mixture.
Spoon potato mixture into shells. Sprinkle with both cheeses.
Place potatoes on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° until potatoes are piping hot and cheese is melted, about 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: herb mayonnaise vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except sour cream.
Mix well and fold in sour cream.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: 9-day old slaw
directions: Mix together cabbage, green pepper, onion and 1 to 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Set aside.
Blend remaining ingredients and bring to a full boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
Pour over cabbage mixture immediately.
Let cool.
Cover and store in the refrigerator.
Keeps 9 days.

title: easy lemon pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add sugar and stir in marshmallows while still hot.
Add lemon juice.
Let cool some. Add pineapple, cottage cheese, salt and nuts.
Stir until well mixed.
Add softened Cool Whip.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into mold or bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken a la king
directions: For sauce, in a saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk, 1 cup water and chicken bouillon granules, all at once.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir for 1 to 2 minutes more.
Stir in chicken, mushroom stems and pieces (drained) and pimiento.
Heat through. Serve spooned over toast, toasted English muffins or baked patty shells.
Serves 4.

title: carbonnades 'a la flamande
directions: Cook bacon until brown.
Put bacon in 3-quart casserole dish. In bacon grease, cook onions until tender and lightly brown. Place with bacon in dish.
In grease, cook beef chunks until browned on all sides.
Add salad oil if necessary.
Put in dish.

title: toffee crunch
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Put a layer of saltines (1/4 pound) on sheet.
Boil 2 sticks of butter with 1 cup of sugar for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Sprinkle a large package of milk chocolate chips on top.
Spread when melted.
Cut long way into strips. Chill.
Finish cutting crossways.

title: one step brownies
directions: Put all of the ingredients into bowl and mix all together. Mix about 4 minutes or until smooth.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes (greased pan).

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a single layer in a shallow baking pan. Add the sauce mixture.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 325°.
Uncover and bake 45 minutes.
Baste occasionally.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Blend soup and milk.
Combine all ingredients, using only half of cheese.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add enough broth to be moist.
Bake at 375°, about 40 minutes, or until golden brown.
More broth can be added while baking.
Spoon over the top.

title: walnut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Sift first 3 ingredients into a bowl. Add butter and mix well.
Stir in walnuts.
Drop on baking sheet and bake until light golden brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Put in greased and floured pan in order given.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chicken piccata(may use green rice as side dish)
directions: Melt the butter in a large skillet; heat to medium high.
Roll chicken breasts in flour.
Cut each breast in half or smaller pieces.
Brown chicken in butter for 5 minutes; turn chicken, then pour in lemon juice, cooking wine and garlic.
Cover; let cook on medium heat for 5 minutes.
Remove chicken and garnish with fresh parsley.
Remaining butter makes a good sauce for chicken or rice.

title: philly apricot cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and cream cheese well.
Add eggs, juice and peel.
Add flour and baking powder.
Chill several hours.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter; add gradually sugar; mix well.
Blend in chocolate; add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each addition.
Turn into cooled, baked pie shell.
Chill 1 to 2 hours before serving with whipped cream and walnuts.

title: never failing biscuits
directions: Mix the water, yeast and sugar.
Stir to dissolve; add the oil, buttermilk, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add the flour one cup at a time, mixing well after each cup.
Cover mixing bowl with a plate or foil and refrigerate overnight or a few hours.
Each time you wish to use some, stir dough lightly; cut off the amount you want.
Knead on floured board or wax paper.
Cut off rolls and bake at 450° until brown, about 15 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine condensed milk, limeade concentrate and whipped topping in a bowl; mix well. Spoon into pie shell. Chill for 10 minutes or until serving time. May substitute lemonade concentrate for limeade concentrate, if desired. Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate cake with black walnut cream filling
directions: Place sugar, milk, egg yolks, flour and butter in double boiler.
Cook until custard forms.
After custard cools, add nuts and vanilla.
Spread between layers.
Cover with chocolate frosting.

title: easy coconut custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Pour into a well-greased 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with coconut, as desired.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: meal-in-one
directions: Cook macaroni by package directions.
Saute onions in butter. Cook ground beef.
Combine all ingredients together except the Cheddar cheese in large greased dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: turtle cake
directions: In saucepan, over low heat, melt caramels with butter and milk.
Mix cake according to directions.
Pour half of batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; top with chocolate chips and pecans. Pour caramel mixture over the first layer after baking it.
Pour second half of cake batter over top.
Bake 20 minutes more.
May frost, if desired.
May be prepared a couple of days in advance.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons melted butter until smooth. Add chicken, milk, salt, pepper and pimento.
Mix well. Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles. Firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture into center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to top center of filling; twist slightly and seal edges.
(May be frozen at this point.) Brush tops with 1 tablespoon butter. Sprinkle crouton crumbs.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes until brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: toffee squares
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolk and vanilla; blend together.
Add flour, mix together again.
Spread this mixture onto a cookie sheet by pinching pieces of dough and pressing dough to cover the cookie sheet, working with your fingers.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° oven.

title: crispy critters
directions: Melt the chips, peanut butter and butter in the top of a double boiler.
Remove from heat and stir in the Rice Krispies. You can either drop the mixture by teaspoons on waxed paper or spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut into bars when cool.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Wash blueberries and sprinkle with sugar.
Place blueberries and crushed pineapple in a large baking dish.
Sprinkle cake mix over top of berries.
Melt margarine and pour over cake mix.
Top with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
and roll into marble size balls. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: broccoli cheese cornbread
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Should be golden brown.

title: hamburger chili dip
directions: Mix into crock-pot, set on low.
Cook about 1 hour until hot. Serve with chips.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook all except cheese and milk for 3 minutes.
Add heated milk and cheese, cut in chunks.
Stir until cheese melts (4 minutes).
Can be frozen.
When reheating, thin with canned chicken broth.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: Empty all of the ingredients into a mixing bowl.
Mix it all together with an electric mixer.
Chill in the refrigerator.
You can put it on crackers or stuff celery with it.

title: gooey butter coffee cake
directions: Blend cake mix, 2 eggs and butter.
Place in a large ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cheese, vanilla, 2 eggs and powdered sugar (save 2 tablespoons). Pour mixture on top of the first layer. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Then sprinkle nuts and remaining powdered sugar.
Bake an additional 25 minutes.

title: onion soup
directions: Melt butter in a 4-quart soup pot. Saute onions slowly for about 40 minutes or until brown. Add flour and mix well. Cover and steam about 5 minutes.

title: jamay's biscuit peach cobbler
directions: Bake biscuits as directed on can.
In a 3-quart pot, add peaches, sugar, butter, nutmeg, cloves, cinnamon, vanilla and lemon flavor.
Cook until it starts to get thick.
Break open your cooked biscuits and place the bottom part on a greased square pan. Pour your peach mixture over the biscuit bottom, then place the top part of the biscuit over the mixture.
Let bake in hot oven for 15 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or cheese, if desired. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate hazelnut truffle log(makes one log)
directions: Melt over hot, not boiling, water, chocolate morsels; stir until smooth.
Remove from heat but keep over hot water.
Add butter, egg yolks and heavy cream; beat with a wire whisk or fork until smooth.
Stir in hazelnut flavored liqueur.
Transfer to a small bowl.
Set bowl over larger bowl filled with ice cubes. Chill, stirring occasionally, until fudgelike in consistency yet smooth and creamy, about 30 minutes.
Shape into 8-inch log.
Roll in hazelnuts.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine soup, water and cheese.
Over low heat, heat until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Add spaghetti, chicken, pepper and parsley.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: aunt millie's cheese cake
directions: Grease and flour spring-form pan.
All ingredients must be at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients in one large bowl.
Mix well.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix
sugars
and Crisco together well.
Add eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Stir
in
nuts.
Add flour, soda, salt and spices which have been sifted together.
Blend well.
Mixture will be very
stiff;
shape
into
about 2 1/2-inch rolls and place in refrigerator.
When
ready to bake, slice and bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.
Bake on greased cookie sheets.
Remove while warm.
Makes at least 5 dozen cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place the cut up chicken, dipped in melted butter, in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour remaining ingredients over chicken. Sprinkle onion soup over the top.
Cover with foil and bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cornstarch and water; mix.
Bring to boil; simmer 15 minutes, then add cornstarch and water.
Mix and simmer until desired thickness.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Melt
oleo and saute celery and onion.
Mix with cooked rice; add chicken,
mushroom
soup,
Cheez
Whiz
and drained broccoli. Bake at 350° in casserole dish for 30 minutes.

title: mayme's cheese dreams
directions: Toast lightly the 8 slices of bread.
Precook bacon lightly. Place cheese, tomatoes and onion on bread.
Broil approximately 2 minutes.
Place cooked bacon on top of mixture and broil until cheese is melted.
Serve with your favorite salad.

title: sunny pasta salad
directions: Boil noodles as directed on package. Drain water. Slice peppers, onion (or chop), olives and pepperoni. Mix in with noodles. Pour whole bottle of dressing over mixture. Toss well. Chill and serve.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat oil over high heat.
Add dash of garlic salt.
Cut chicken in strips; add to oil.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Add vegetables; stir-fry 3 more minutes.
Reduce heat; stir in the remaining ingredients.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: california granola
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except raisins and mix well.
Spread onto ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown, stirring occasionally.
Stir in raisins.
Spread onto ungreased cookie sheet or aluminum foil; cool.
Store in tightly covered container in refrigerator.
Serves as a snack or as cereal with milk.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: pudding surprise cake
directions: Leave baked cake in deep large 9 x 13 or size larger pan.
Add mixed banana cream pudding.
Layer with Cool Whip.
Top with cherry or strawberry pie filling.

title: pear oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter with brown sugar until smooth.
Beat in remaining ingredients, except sugar, until combined.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle generously with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: garbanzo bean soup
directions: Heat beans and tomatoes together in large cooker.
Cook onion and hamburger together.
Pour in with beans and tomatoes.
Simmer for 4 hours.

title: zucchini relish(canning)
directions: Combine zucchini, onion, green and red peppers.
Sprinkle with salt and cover with cold water.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain vegetables; press out liquid.
Combine remaining ingredients, bring to a boil.
Add vegetables, simmer 10 minutes.
Pour hot into hot jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 4 1/2 pints.

title: cinnamon french toast(kindergarten recipe)
directions: You break the eggs and mix in cinnamon with a fork real good. Add milk.
Put a piece of bread in and then put it into a buttered pan.
(Do all 4 pieces.)
Flip it over, take it out.
Put it on a plate and put syrup on top.
Then you eat it.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Fill each greased cupcake cup 2/3 full.
Cream together the cheese, salt, sugar and egg until light and fluffy.
Stir in chocolate bits.
Drop a tablespoon of this mixture on top of each cupcake.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cream mixture will be in the center of each cake.
These may be frosted with chocolate icing, if desired.

title: bake-a-rice
directions: Cook sausage, then drain.
Boil soup mix and rice for 7 minutes in water.
Add vegetables; put in baking dish.
Cover with water chestnuts, then bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy rocky road
directions: Butter 8-inch square pan.
In large microwave-safe bowl, place chocolate chips, butter and shortening.
Microwave at High (100%) for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes just until chocolate chips are melted and mixture is smooth when stirred.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Blend well.
Spread even in prepared pan.
Cover and refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 16 squares.

title: meatballs in sauce
directions: Mix.
Form into small balls (walnut size).
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Turn as needed.
Prepare sauce.

title: potato deluxe(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Mix all together. Pour into oblong pan. Sprinkle with corn flakes, crumbled. Bake 1 hour or more at 375° until brown on top. Serve for breakfast, lunch or dinner with entree and salad.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion in skillet.
Drain grease. Add salt, pepper and chili powder.
Simmer over low heat and add cream of mushroom and tomato soups.
Simmer about 5 minutes and pour meat mixture over cooked macaroni.
Sprinkle crushed cracker crumbs over the top and sprinkle heavily with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 450° for about 10 minutes or until ingredients are heated through and sauce bubbles.
Serves 5.

title: bul-kogi(korean barbecue)
directions: Place in broiler pan, cover and let marinate at least 15 minutes or until ready to cook.
Uncover and broil about 10 minutes.
Serve over white rice.

title: streusel topped fruit pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Pour pie filling into pie shell.
In bowl combine flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly; stir in nuts.
Crumble this mixture over pie filling. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until top is golden brown and filling is bubbly.
Remove from oven and let cool.

title: oriental beef
directions: Fry ground beef, onions and mushrooms together and drain. Return the meat mixture to the skillet.
Put green beans in a strainer and run water over them to separate.
Stir the beans and rice into the beef mixture.
Push the skillet mixture to the sides of the skillet.
Break the egg into the center and scramble.
Mix the meat mixture and scrambled egg together.
Add soy sauce and stir-fry until the mixture is heated.
Serve from the skillet.

title: easy skillet chicken
directions: Beat egg and milk together.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken into egg mixture; roll in flour mixture.
Brown chicken well, in a mixture of oil and butter, in a heavy skillet.
Pour off skillet drippings.
Return chicken to skillet.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water.
Cover.
Cook over low heat for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Soak pieces in buttermilk overnight in refrigerator.
Drain.
The next day, dip in flour, salt and pepper.
Fry as usual.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Let simmer as long as possible before serving.

title: spicy shrimp with noodles
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions, while cleaning the shrimp; drain. Melt butter in a medium skillet over low heat. Stir in olive oil and red pepper flakes and raise heat to medium-high. Add shrimp and saute until almost pink. Add Cajun seasoning and garlic powder; saute for 1 minute until fragrant. Add Italian seasoning and sherry; heat until simmering. Dissolve cornstarch in water; add to skillet. Continue to cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. If necessary add small amounts of additional sherry until desired consistency is reached. Top with Parmesan cheese. Serve hot over linguine.

title: orange yogurt salad
directions: Pour water over gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Stir in yogurt and orange segments.
Pour into 4-cup mold.
Chill until firm, at least 4 hours; unmold.
Makes 8 servings, about 1/2 cup each.

title: today's cornbread
directions: Mix together; beat until smooth.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: oatmeal raisin spice cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, shortening, eggs and water in a large bowl; blend
thoroughly.
Stir
in oats and raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls
onto
ungreased
cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix Cool Whip, sour cream and sugar; add all other ingredients.
Freeze.
Take out 1 hour before serving.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Put rice in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and place chicken on top of it.
Mix together the water and cream of mushroom soup.
Pour over the chicken.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix; cover with foil and bake at 350° for about an hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: texas chili
directions: Mix the ingredients and soak the ribs in this mixture for 2 hours.
Then bake in oven at 300° for 2 or 3 hours.
Baste every now and then with the sauce.
If the ribs are fatty, drop them in boiling water for about 5 minutes before marinating, then proceed as directed.
Serves 6.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter bottom of 9 X 13 pan. Spread pie filling evenly over bottom of pan. Sprinkle cake mix evenly over top of filling. Sprinkle nuts and butter over top. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. When completely cooled, spread with cool whip. Keep refrigerated.

title: white christmas cake
directions: In a large saucepan, bring margarine or butter and 3/4 cup water to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add baking bar; stir until melted.
Stir in buttermilk, eggs and rum extract; set aside.
Sir together 1/2 cup of the flour and the pecans; set aside.
In an extra bowl, stir together remaining 3 cups flour, sugar, coconut, soda and powder.
Stir in margarine mixture.
Fold in coconut mixture.
Stir in margarine mixture. Fold in pecan mixture.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken
until tender; debone and cut into pieces.
Mix chicken,
soup, green chilies, and sour cream together.

title: garlic bread
directions: Mix all ingredients with enough mayonnaise to hold together (not too much).
Spread evenly over bread or buns.
Place under broiler until melted.

title: pecan cheese bars
directions: Combine butter, sugar and corn syrup.
Cook over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Cool slightly.
Add beaten eggs gradually.
Add vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 325 degrees for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken casserole #2
directions: Place drained peas on bottom of 9 x 12-inch casserole dish. Spread chicken over this.
Make sauce of soup, mayonnaise and water.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle on almonds.
Tear bread into small pieces and place on top.
Drizzle melted margarine over bread.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat yolks and whites separately.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to yolks while beating.
Add 1/4 cup sugar to whites after beaten stiff. Mix yolks and whites, add milk, whipped cream, whiskey and rum. Let set for at least 2 hours.
Stir before serving.

title: three-cheese potato souffle
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first nine ingredients. Beat egg yolks; stir into potato mixture. In a small mixing bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; gently fold into potato mixture. Transfer to a 2-qt. souffle dish coated with nonstick cooking spray. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 - 45 minutes or until golden. Serve immediately.

title: eggplant appetizer
directions: Wash eggplant; cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
In 1/2 cup hot oil in large skillet, saute eggplant until tender and golden brown. Remove eggplant and set aside.
In 2 tablespoons hot oil in same skillet, saute onion and celery until tender, about 5 minutes. Return eggplant to skillet.
Stir in tomato sauce; bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Add vinegar, sugar, capers, salt, pepper and olives.
Simmer, covered, and stirring occasionally, 20 minutes longer.
Refrigerate eggplant mixture, covered, overnight.

title: ranch pudding
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix in saucepan 1 cup brown sugar, water and butter.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour into 9-inch square pan.
Mix in bowl 1 cup brown sugar, milk, Bisquick, raisins, nuts and vanilla. Spoon batter on top of mixture.
It will sink into liquid and spread as it bakes.
Bake 45 minutes.
Serve warm, plain or with whipped cream.
This recipe serves 9.

title: jalapeno fudge
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Put chilies evenly in greased 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle cheese over chilies.
Pour eggs over cheese and bake until firm in center, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Place on wire rack and cool 5 minutes.
Cut into bite size pieces. Delicious served on crackers.

title: cap'n crunch cookies
directions: Melt almond bark.
Add all other ingredients.
Drop on wax paper.

title: chapatis
directions: This is a flat bread.
Sift flour and salt, adding 2 tablespoons oil and 2/3 cup water.
Stir to form a ball.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 3 minutes.
Divide into 12 equal pieces and form into balls.
Roll into circles 6 to 7-inches; keep covered.
Heat a cast-iron skillet and cook in ungreased skillet 1 minute on each side.
Stack and cover with towel.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together, except cornflakes.
Pour into baking dish and top with crushed cornflakes.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo and pour over slivered almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Delicious with cooked rice.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Mix until crumbly.
Press into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fudgemallow candy
directions: Melt chocolate with peanut butter in saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Fold in marshmallows.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: "fast and easy" chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken and eggs together; put in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix broth and soup together; pour over chicken.
Mix flour, milk and melted margarine; pour over casserole.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Blend well.
Pour in an 8 x 12-inch greased casserole.
Add bread crumbs, sausage and cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hobo bread
directions: Combine raisins, water and baking soda.
Let stand overnight (10 to 14 hours).
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix by hand with spoon.
Grease cans (not too large) and fill each can 1/2 full. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cool in cans, when cool, remove from cans.
Wrap in plastic wrap or freeze.
You may use soup cans or any other size you wish.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and spoon onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: raisin cinnamon bars(i use dates instead of raisins.)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir into creamed mixture; add oats and 1 tablespoon water.
Mix until crumbly.
Firmly pat 1/2 mixture in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread with date filling.
Mix remaining crumbs and 1 tablespoon water.
Spoon over filling.
Pat smooth.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.
Cool; drizzle with Cinnamon Icing.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pimento and cheese
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix in other ingredients.
(Black pepper, garlic and mayonnaise are used to your taste.)

title: wilted lettuce dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Pour over cut up leaf lettuce.
Mix enough to coat lettuce.

title: swedish pound cake
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well after each.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and stir in.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken ala can
directions: Make in large frying pan.
Put soup, water and rice in pan. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add all ingredients except onion rings, and simmer 10 minutes.
Heat onion rings in oven.
Dish up chicken hot dish into serving bowl and put onion rings on top.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions with margarine in large skillet for 15 to 20 minutes on medium heat.
Place half of onions in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with half of crackers and half of Parmesan cheese.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: beef and vegetable casserole
directions: Brown onions in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add meat and seasoning. Heat until meat loses color.
Put in casserole dish over green beans.
Add tomato soup.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
More spices can be added to taste.
Pans should not be over 1/2 full.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Melt butter and beat eggs.
Drain the whole kernel corn. Combine all ingredients together, adding the muffin mix last.
Pour mixture into a greased 7 X 11-inch baking dish.
Bake ate 375 degrees for 35-40 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pasta-bean salad
directions: Cook the pasta (macaroni, twists or shells) and drain.
In large bowl, stir together mayonnaise, parsley, cheese and lemon juice until blended.
Add pasta, beans, peas and carrots; toss to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: molded spring salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Beat in salad dressing with mixer.
Stir in cottage cheese and add salt.
Chill until thick and syrupy.
Fold in peas, radishes, green peppers and onion. Pour into lightly oiled mold.
Chill until set.

title: light trifle
directions: Prepare instant pudding according to package directions.
Fold in half the whipped topping while pudding is still soft.

title: casserole of chicken and dressing
directions: Spread 1/2 of bread cubes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix chicken, celery, onion and mayonnaise and spread over cubes. Cover with remaining cubes.
Combine eggs and milk and pour over top.
Let stand overnight, refrigerated.
Mix soup and 1/2 can of milk and pour over top before baking.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle cheese over top for last 10 minutes of baking.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles per package directions.
Rinse under cold water. Add remaining ingredients and toss gently.

title: chicken deluxe casserole
directions: Mix stuffing and butter together.
Press half of mixture in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baker.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour over stuffing.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder and sugar.
Add milk and well beaten egg.
Mix well.
Pare and core apples, cut in sections and dip each piece of apple in the butter.
Fry in deep fat until brown.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in water over double boiler until chocolate melts; cool.
Sift flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Beat egg yolks with sour cream, adding sugar gradually, and beat vigorously until thick.
Add chocolate mixture and vanilla mixing well.
Add flour, soda and salt to sour cream mixture.
Beat until smooth. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in paper lined 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Frost with chocolate butter cream frosting.

title: 1-2-3 beer bread
directions: Mix in beer 4 ounces at a time.
Pour the batter into 3 well-greased 3 x 6-inch pans.
Drizzle melted butter over the top. Bake for about 50 minutes at 350°.
Good at barbecues.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix together and let congeal.

title: jan hagel cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease jelly roll pan.
Mix oleo, sugar and egg yolk.
Blend in flour and cinnamon.
Pat into pan. Beat egg white and water; brush over dough.
Sprinkle with nuts. Bake 20 to 25 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cut immediately into strips.

title: peggy's carrot-pineapple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add eggs and crushed pineapple.
Beat well. Mix dry ingredients together and add to other mixture.
Add carrots and pecans and beat well.
Bake in three 9-inch greased and floured pans about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Wash and cut rhubarb into small 1-inch pieces.
Beat egg; add lemon juice, sugar and flour.
Mix together and pour over chopped rhubarb.
Stir until well coated.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie crust.
Dot with oleo.
Cover with top crust.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar and prick holes with fork.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes and then at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cabbage supreme
directions: Boil shredded cabbage for 7 minutes. Grate the cheese.
Make white sauce with the margarine, flour, milk and salt.
Line buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish with finely crushed potato chips. Add 1/2 of the cooked cabbage, 1/2 of the white sauce mix and sliced hard-boiled eggs.
Spread 1/3 cup grated cheese over mixture. Repeat steps, ending with the remaining chips. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: christmas ornaments(do not eat!)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Knead in bowl until thoroughly blended.
Lightly spray dough board and rolling pin and roll mixture to 1/2 inch thick.
If dough sticks, spray a sheet of waxed paper and place over mixture.
Cut out with cookie cutters. Using a straw, punch a hole in each ornament where you will put the ribbon later.
Lay out to dry for at least 2 days.
Tie ribbon through holes and hang on tree.

title: raspberry nut bread(mmmmmm-good)
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together the berries, sour cream and nuts.
Add alternately the dry ingredients to the liquid ingredients.
Grease and flour loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: holiday garlic olives
directions: Drain olives; save liquid.
In small saucepan, combine 1 cup olive liquid, chili powder, garlic, bay leaves, olive oil, pepper and onion.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes, uncovered.
Stir in pimientos.
Place olives in a large jar; pour seasoning mixture over.
Cover.
Refrigerate.
Make at least 3 to 4 days prior to serving.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: glazed meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine ground beef, bread crumbs, milk, egg, onion, 2 tablespoons tomato sauce, horseradish, salt and pepper. Mix well. Put in loaf pan. Combine remaining ingredients and spread over meat loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix wafers and butter and spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Arrange sliced bananas over crust.
Beat together milk and lemon juice until thick.
Add sour cream.
Pour over bananas.
Mix together pineapple and Cool Whip and spread over sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle with pecans, coconut and cherries.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: sweet and sour baked beans
directions: Place onions in skillet; add sugar, mustard, garlic salt, salt and vinegar.
Cook 20 minutes, covered.
Add onion mixture to beans.
Add bacon.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12.
This fills a 3-quart casserole.

title: corn casserole
directions: If you have difficulty finding yellow rice, use white rice.

title: cupid cream puffs
directions: In a medium saucepan, heat butter with water over high heat, stirring occasionally, until butter is melted and mixture is boiling. Add salt and flour all at once. Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture leaves sides of pan in a smooth compact ball. Remove from heat.
Quickly add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition until smooth and shiny.
Drop mixture by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet, 3-inches apart, shaping each into a mound.
Bake in a 400° oven 50 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: hearty stir-fry
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
In medium skillet, cook sausage until no longer pink.
Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Add cabbage, onion, apple and garlic.
Stir-fry just until tender.
Stir in next 4 ingredients. Add spaghetti.
Cook and stir until hot.
Remove from heat.
Add cheeses; toss to mix.
Arrange on warm serving platter.
Garnish as desired.
Serve immediately.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: meatballs and sauerkraut
directions: Mix together meat, egg, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Simmer catsup, water and cookie crumbs for 5 minutes.
Add brown sugar, salt and sauerkraut.
Heat to boiling. Add meatballs; lower heat and simmer for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter, sugar and salt gradually and add milk until it starts to thicken.
Beat eggs and then stir them in.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes, peppers and onions fine.
Boil all together slowly, then add spices and sugar and boil 3 to 4 hours.
Bottle and seal while hot.

title: cucumber casserole
directions: *You can use half ground beef and half sausage.

title: summer vegetable tian(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Blanch the broccoli in salted, boiling water for 3 minutes or until it is bright green.
Refresh under cold water and allow to drain.
Trim the tough stalks from the spinach and wash well, without draining the spinach.
Put the spinach in a large pot and cook over low heat, covered, until wilted, about 4 to 5 minutes. Squeeze out the water and chop roughly.
Set aside.

title: brownies from heaven
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time,
beating well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla. Combine flour and cocoa; add to creamed mixture just until combined.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 23-28 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: cherry cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Line with graham crackers (not crushed).
Mix together pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour half of this mixture over graham crackers.
Place another layer of graham crackers over this and pour rest of the pudding mixture over crackers.
Lay a third layer of graham crackers on top.
Frost top layer with Fudge Frosting and let set all day or night in refrigerator.

title: hoppin john soup
directions: Fry sausage and drain.
Drain 3 cans of peas; use juice and all of the other 3 cans.
In a 6-quart pot, stir in peas, onions, salt, pepper, water and sausage.
Bring to a boil and cook on medium for 45 minutes.
Add cooked rice and simmer 20 minutes more.
The soup will be thick, so stir frequently to keep from sticking.

title: asparagus-almond casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Toast bread; crumble and mix with butter. Combine cheese and soup. Heat slightly to melt cheese. Add almonds. Place half the asparagus in prepared dish. Cover with slices of 1 egg and half of the soup mixture. Repeat layer. Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs over all. Bake until bubbly and browned, about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water just enough to separate.
In bowl, combine soup, mayonnaise, beaten eggs, onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour this into broccoli, mixing well.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Melt margarine and mix into stuffing; sprinkle on top of broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Combine softened cheese, strawberries and sugar.
Process until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream and freeze in pie shell.
Top with additional frozen or fresh strawberries to decorate.

title: maw, maw rene's banana pudding
directions: Combine cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk, beating on low speed until well blended.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix.
Beat on low speed 1 minute.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding mix until all used, ending with top layer of pudding.
Cover with a layer of Dream Whip.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: panamanian chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow pan and pour other ingredients over chicken.
Cook covered in oven at 375° for 1 hour.

title: aunt wanda chicken
directions: Heat enough oil in a skillet to cover the bottom. Salt tenderloins. Dredge in flour. Lightly brown both sides in oil. Pour off some of the oil before next step. Generously sprinkle tenderloins with lemon pepper seasoning. Mix soup and 1/2 can of hot water and pour over tenderloins. Sprinkle with a little more lemon pepper seasoning. Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: crunchy romaine toss
directions: Brown in skillet walnuts, Ramen noodles, butter, and almond slices.

Set aside and cool. In a large salad bowl, combine broccoli, romaine lettuce, chopped green onions. Mix together oil, sugar or Splenda, vinegar, soy sauce, and salt and pepper to make dressing. To romaine mixture add nut mixture and toss.
Pour dressing over salad mixture and toss.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Wash strawberries and sprinkle with salt and let drain.
Bake pie shell and let cool.
Cook 7-Up, sugar, cornstarch and food coloring until thick and clear.
Cool.
Add strawberries and pour into pie shell.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with the syrup.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in a sheet cake pan which has been floured and greased at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare cake as directed on box. Combine water, orange juice and food coloring.
Add grated orange peel; mix.
Bake and cool as directed on box.

title: lana's peasant bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine water, yeast, sugar and salt.
Stir until dissolved.
Add flour (dough will be wet).
Place dough onto floured platter.

title: light and easy lemon chicken
directions: Place each chicken breast in the center of a 12-inch square piece of aluminum foil.
Fold sides of foil up so the lemon juice won't run out.
Halve the lemons and squeeze the juice of 1/2 lemon over each chicken breast, then sprinkle each with 1/4 teaspoon tarragon and black pepper.
(I also add 1/2 to 1 teaspoon of wine, poured over each piece of chicken.)
Fold foil together and seal well.
Bake wrapped chicken in shallow baking dish at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peasant potatoes
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, melt butter.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook and stir 5 minutes or until onion is transparent. Stir in oregano and sausage and cook about 5 minutes more.
Stir in potatoes, salt and pepper until potatoes are well coated with butter.
Place mixture in slow cooker.
Cover and cook on High 3 to 4 hours or on low for 6 to 8 hours, stirring every hour if possible.
During last 30 minutes of cooking, add cabbage and peppers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.
Makes 6 side dish servings or 4 main dish servings.

title: coconut one step pie
directions: Blend all ingredients well. Pour into greased pie tin.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: texas stew
directions: Brown
ground
beef in a large skillet.
Drain.
Mix in can of	tomato	sauce,	corn,
green
beans, new potatoes and spices. Let simmer on stove for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with corn bread.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Mix the crumbs, butter and seasonings.
Sprinkle a layer of crumb mixture 1/2 inch thick in the bottom of a buttered baking dish.
Cover with oysters.
Add a little milk, then a layer of crumb mixture.
Repeat until all the mixture has been used.
Be sure a layer of crumbs is on top.
Bake 35 minutes in a moderate oven.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix all and shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 11 minutes on ungreased baking sheets.
"Do not overcook."
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: pineapple cocktail barbecue
directions: Drain pineapple and save syrup.
Combine the syrup with the jelly or preserves, ketchup, cloves, cinnamon and salt.
Heat to boiling.

title: fruit ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Place in ice cream churn to freeze.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift the dry ingredients and add to the cream mixture, mixing well.
Fold in the mashed bananas, vanilla and walnuts.
Pour into the prepared pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until a tester inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool in the pan for 2 minutes, then invert on a rack.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Spread pineapple in a lightly buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; sprinkle with cake mix, blueberries and sugar. Drizzle with butter and top with pecans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: microwave curried rice with almonds
directions: Put onions and oil into 3-quart casserole. Cover tightly and microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes. Wash rice briefly in a sieve under cold, running water; drain well.
Add to onions in a casserole along with rest of ingredients, except almonds. Cover tightly
and microwave on High for 7 minutes; stir.
Cover and microwave until liquid is almost absorbed, 8 to 10 minutes longer. Stir. Cover and let stand 10 minutes.
Stir again and top with almonds.

title: ice cream sandwich dessert
directions: Unwrap ice cream sandwiches and place side by side in a 13 x 9 pan. Top with caramel topping, nuts and Cool Whip. Freeze until ready to serve. Cut into squares to serve.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in small bowl; spread on 1 slice of bread.
Top with remaining bread to form a sandwich.
In small bowl, beat egg with water.
Transfer to small, shallow pan and soak sandwich, turning occasionally, for 10 minutes or until all egg is absorbed.
Melt margarine in small skillet; add sandwich. Cook until bottom is golden brown; turn and brown other side.
Top with strawberry spread and serve.
Serves 1.

title: uncooked chili sauce
directions: Bring vegetables, spices, sugar and vinegar to a boil and fill 10 pint jars.
Seal.
The liquid that you drain off can be put in tomato juice if making it the next day.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: In a bowl, combine the first seven ingredients. Add beef and mix well. Shape into 1-1/2 inch balls. In a large skillet, brown meatballs in oil; drain. Combine tomato sauce, water, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce; pour over meatballs. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: frosty lemon supreme(healthful eating)
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with 1/4 cup of the graham cracker crumbs.
Beat egg whites, water and milk to stiff peaks.
Add egg yolks, lemon zest and lemon juice; beat 1 minute, gradually adding sugar.
Spoon into pie plate.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top. Freeze at least 2 hours.

title: doughboys
directions: Wrap cubes of ham and cheese in biscuits.
Toast on grill. Serve with pickle relish.

title: cheese ball
directions: Leave cream cheese at room temperature. Mix with onions that are chopped real fine.
Cut up corn beef with scissors and mix in. Add Accent and Worcestershire sauce.
Roll ball in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: crescent lasagna rolls
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage, stirring until crumbly.
Add onions, spices, tomato paste and garlic.
Mix well.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes and cool.
Combine egg, cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese in bowl and mix well.
Press crescent rolls into two 3 x 10-inch rectangles.
Layer ground beef mixture, egg and cheese mixture and Mozzarella cheese on rectangles.
Roll each to enclose filling.
Place on baking sheet.
Brush with milk.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn pudding(serve as a vegetable.)
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth.
Add eggs, corn, butter and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place in pan of hot water.
Bake at 300° for 1 3/4 hours.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: chinese sauteed fresh vegetables
directions: *Choose any 1 vegetable or combine several.
Vegetables should total 1 pound before cooking.

title: herb-roasted potatoes
directions: Cut the vegetables into chunks.
Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients in shallow baking pan in a single layer.
Bake for 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a large saucepan.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Cook hamburger, bell peppers and onion.
Add cheese.
Add to meal, corn, oil, milk and salt.
Mix all together and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: griffin's grape jelly meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, crumbs, onion, milk, egg, and next four seasonings;
Gently shape into 1-inch balls, melt shortening in large skillet.
Brown meatballs.
Remove meatballs from skillet, drain fat.
Heat chili sauce & jelly in skillet until jelly is melted, stirring constantly,
Add meatballs & stir until coated. Simmer 30 mins.
Serve hot in chafing dish.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: taco bake
directions: Cook ground beef with onions until browned and drain well. Spoon into a 13 x 9-inch ungreased baking dish.
Into this stir taco seasoning, drained corn and tomato sauce.
Spread evenly in dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup shredded cheese on top.
Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs until well blended.
Pour over beef mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Serve with lettuce, tomato, salsa and sour cream.

title: blender hollandaise sauce
directions: Heat butter until bubbly.
Place egg yolks, lemon juice and salt in blender.
Blend at low speed.
Uncover.
Pour hot butter in.
Continue to blend.
Makes 1/3 cup.

title: spanish stew
directions: *The more celery, peppers and onions the better.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix sugar and syrup and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter mix.
Add cornflakes and stir until all are coated with syrup mixture.
Drop by teaspoon into wax paper.
Cool and serve.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Dissolve soda in milk; add flour alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Roll nuts, candy and dates in extra flour, then add coconut.
Add to cake batter.
Bake in tube pan at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.
Mix 2 cups white sugar, and 1 cup orange juice; pour on cake while hot.
Store cake in pan overnight.
Can also bake in loaf pans.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Mix 1 egg with box of cake mix and 1/4 cup butter (melted). Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press mixture into the bottom.
Mix 2 eggs, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Pour on top of other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain squash and combine all other ingredients.
Set aside enough stuffing or topping.
Bake in casserole dish 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter two large cookie sheets.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating constantly until stiff and glossy.
Fold in vanilla, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto a buttered cookie sheet.
Put in preheated oven, then turn oven off.
Leave in oven for several hours or overnight until crisp.

title: richs celery chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle tenderloins with salt and pepper.
Brown in skillet in butter about 5 minutes per side.
Remove.
Cook onion and celery in same skillet until tender; add more butter if needed. Remove.
Add flour and 1 Tbsp. butter to skillet.
Stir over medium heat until paste forms.
Add chicken broth to skillet. Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in celery and onion. Layer rice in casserole.
Layer chicken pieces over rice.
Pour thickened celery broth over meat.
Cover and bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread blueberry mix over pineapple.
Spread dry cake mix over blueberries. Cut margarine into pats and lay on cake mix. Sprinkle nuts on top of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. May top with whipping cream.

title: orange candy cake
directions: Use some extra flour to coat candy and nuts.

title: hot slaw
directions: Put cabbage and onions in large bowl.
Heat remaining ingredients in saucepan, bringing to a boil.
Pour over cabbage and onions; toss.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and have noodles cooked and drained.
Melt butter. Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add broth.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
