Pour in a greased casserole.

title: pretzel salad
directions: 1st Layer:
Add melted butter to pretzels and sugar; mix well and bake for 6 minutes.
Let cool while preparing 2nd layer.

title: beefed-up chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place dried beef slices evenly around chicken breasts.
Tuck edges of beef under chicken. Place in 8-inch square baking dish. Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and sprinkle with almonds. Continue baking at 350° for 15 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry meringue cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper.
Combine egg whites and salt in a large bowl.
Beat with an electric mixer on a medium-high speed until soft peaks form, 1 to 2 minutes.
Increase speed to high.
Add sugar gradually in a slow steady stream, beating until stiff, shiny peaks form, 2 to 4 minutes.
Add strawberry flavoring and food coloring; mix until just combined.
Spoon meringue mixture into pastry bag fitted with star tip.
Pipe meringue into 2-inch mounds on prepared baking sheets.
Bake until cookies are dry and crisp, about 1 hour and 35 minutes.
Turn off oven; let cookies stand in oven with door closed for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool 3 minutes.
Remove from parchment paper; place on wire rack to cool completely.

title: sweet roll dough
directions: In mixing bowl dissolve yeast in water. Stir in milk, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, shortening and half the flour. Stir with spoon. Add the rest of flour. Turn unto floured board. Knead until smooth, about 5 minutes.
Round-up in greased bowl. Cover with damp cloth. Let rise until double, about 1 1/2 hours in warm place. Punch down. Shape into rolls or coffee cake. Let rise until double, about 30 minutes.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients with an electric mixer, then add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put mixture into greased and powdered sugared pans.
Bake for 60 to 90 minutes at 350°. Fill loaf pans half full.

title: salad dressing for spinach salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oil, then add oil slowly until mixed well.

title: banana split cake
directions: Pat graham cracker crumbs, melted margarine and 1 tablespoon sugar in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat 1 egg, soft margarine, salt and confectioners sugar for 10 minutes until very creamy; pour over graham cracker crumbs.
Slice 4 to 5 bananas over mixture.
Drain crushed pineapple; spread over bananas.
Add cut up strawberries over bananas and pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over fruit. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Chill overnight.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix and roll in 1/2 cup nuts.
Chill.
Serve on Ritz crackers.

title: vegetables mexicali
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add zucchini, onion and green pepper and saute for 5 minutes.
Add eggs and stir until barely set.
Remove skillet from heat; stir in chilies, salt, black pepper and cumin.
In a small bowl, blend flour and sour cream.
Arrange 1/2 of tortilla wedges in a shallow 2-quart casserole or 8-inch square baking dish.
Add 1/2 of vegetable mixture, then 1/2 of sour cream mixture.
Top with 1/2 of the cheese.
Repeat layers ending with cheese.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: dean's hot dog chili
directions: Peel and chop onions. In large pot, cover onions with water and boil until onions are soft and mushy. Mix in ground beef, stirring to separate. Add more water, if necessary. Heat until meat is gray. Add tomatoes, mashing with spoon; then add salt, pepper and chili powder. Cook over low heat until thick, stirring often. Skim off excess fat.

title: cocktail bread with cucumber
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together. Spread on slices of rye cocktail bread. Top with a slice of cucumber. Sprinkle with dill weed.

title: misericordia crabcakes
directions: Melt butter and shortening in top of double boiler.
Add onion; let simmer over direct heat about 15 minutes or until onion is very tender, but do not brown or burn it.
Take pan from heat; let cool a moment, then stir in flour.
Be careful the butter mixture is not too hot or the flour will get lumpy.
Stir milk in gradually, making smooth.
Add and stir seasonings.
Place over boiling water and stir constantly until sauce is thickened and well blended. Pour this thick sauce over the picked over crab meat.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Shape the chilled mixture into patties about 1 inch thick.
Roll them in the fine breadcrumbs to coat all over and lower them carefully into hot fat deep enough to cover them completely and fry to a deep golden brown.
Lift out with slotted pancake lifter and let them drain a moment on absorbent paper.
Serve piping hot.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Place rack in middle of oven and preheat to 350°.

title: jumbo oat cookies
directions: Beat sugar, butter or margarine and corn syrup until fluffy. Add egg whites and extract; mix well.
Gradually add combined remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop 1/4 cup measure, about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press into 3-inch circles.
Bake 14 to 16 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute; remove to aluminum foil.
Store lightly covered.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: salsa verde
directions: Peel, core and chop tomatoes. Chop peppers.
Mix all together. Add salt and black pepper to taste.
Bring just to a boil.
Ladle into hot pint jars. Add 1 teaspoon lemon juice and/or vinegar to each jar.
Adjust lids.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; add eggs, food coloring, vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Sift together flour, soda and cocoa. Add the vinegar to the buttermilk.
Alternating, add the flour mixture and the buttermilk to the creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean (15 to 20 minutes).
Use 3 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans or one 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: chinese chews cookie
directions: Mix together butter, brown sugar, eggs, nuts and dates.

title: tomato-topped chicken and stuffing
directions: Crush 1/2 cup stuffing.
In small bowl, combine crushed stuffing and margarine.
Set aside.
In a 3-quart saucepan over high heat, heat water to boiling.
Remove from heat; add remaining stuffing.
Toss to mix well.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Saute onion and garlic.
Add tomatoes, chicken and bouillon, simmer 15 minutes.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Spoon into tortillas, roll up and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Swiss cheese and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise,
curry
powder, soy sauce and lemon juice. Add to chicken mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: cowboy soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions. Mix with all other ingredients in large pot and cook 30 to 45 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix together.
Put in punch bowl.
Add the sherbet at that time.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs.
Add mashed potatoes, sour cream and yeast mixture.
Add flour and salt; knead well.
Brush with melted butter.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Shape in desired form and place on greased pan.
Let rise for 1 hour or more.
Bake in preheated 375° oven about 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Blend all ingredients except crackers. Mix well. Pour over crackers to coat them. Put crackers on a cookie sheet. Place in warm oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese chicken casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter until tender.
Cook noodles and chicken.
Chop the chicken.
Combine onion, celery, water, soup, noodles and chicken.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 cup cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into greased dish and top with remaining cheese.
Cook at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cinnamon and raisin bread(bread machine)
directions: Add ingredients to the bread pan in the order that they are listed except the raisins.
Select setting to Basic.
Change crust color or leave it at medium.
Press Start/Stop to begin.
Add the raisins when beeping sounds during kneading.
Display will read 2:20.
When display read 0:00, press Start/Stop for 3 seconds to cancel.
Use oven mitts to handle hot bread pan.

title: one-step lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Combine beef and spaghetti sauce. Spread 1/3 of mixture in lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange 4 lasagna noodles on sauce.
Layer 1 cup cottage cheese and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese over noodles.
Spoon 1/2 of remaining sauce over cheese.
Top with 4 noodles, 1 cup cottage cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: circuit preacher scripture cake
directions: Follow the directions of Solomon for bringing up a child (Proverbs 23:14).
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for about 1 hour or longer if necessary.
Cool on a rack.
Slices best after a few hours.

title: cheeseburger pie(weight watchers recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown turkey, onion and green pepper in skillet.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic powder. Simmer 8 to 10 minutes.
Add cooked macaroni and 3 ounces of cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch casserole dish that has been sprayed with a nonstick spray. Sprinkle remaining 1 ounce of cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes. Remove and let set 10 to 15 minutes before cutting.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook first 8 ingredients until tender.
Add milk mixed with flour.
Add chicken bouillon cube.
Last, add cubed Velveeta cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix cloves, ginger and cinnamon together in small container. Mix all ingredients, including spices, together. Chill one hour. Shape into balls and roll in sugar. Cookies will flatten in baking.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Stir sugar, milk, butter and cocoa together.
Bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from stove, add oats, peanut butter, nuts and vanilla.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: cobbler dough
directions: Stir with a fork until blended.
Drop by spoonfuls over fruit. Bake in an 8-inch pan for 25 to
30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: peanut butter eggs(easter candy)
directions: Mix well the powdered sugar, peanut butter, margarine, and vanilla.
Form into balls or patties or form mixture into egg shapes; dip in chocolate for Easter.

title: eggplant and yogurt
directions: Fry eggplant until they are golden brown.
Add salt, pepper and water to yogurt.
Take eggplant out of the oil and put cumin seed in the oil until brown.
Put half of the cumin in yogurt.

title: date pudding
directions: Put the hot water and soda over the dates and let stand while you mix up the rest, then put all together.
Cook 1 cup brown sugar and 1 1/2 cups boiling water until sugar dissolves.
Pour over pudding batter before baking.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut crisp bars
directions: Combine sugar, Karo and salt. Cook and stir until sugar is dissolved. Blend in peanut butter. Stir in cereal.
Pat evenly in a foil lined pan.
In small pan, melt oleo and brown sugar. Remove from fire. Add milk and vanilla. Beat in powdered sugar until smooth. Remove cookie mixture from pan.
Peel off foil and spread top with icing.
Chill and cut in small bars.

title: zucchini jelly
directions: Boil grated zucchini and sugar for 6 minutes; add lemon juice, pineapple and Pen-Jell.
Boil 6 minutes more.
Put in sterilized jelly jars.
Melt paraffin and pour on top to seal.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with pineapple and add cottage cheese, Cool Whip and marshmallows. Mix well.

title: frozen coconut pie
directions: Mix well with mixer until soft and creamy.
Pour half of mixture into each pie crust.
Sprinkle coconut mixture over Cool Whip mixture.
Drizzle half caramel topping over coconut mixture. Layer; repeat each mixture again.
Finish with caramel topping. Wrap well and put in freezer overnight.
Keeps well for 3 months in freezer.

title: wieners in a pot
directions: Place dogs in pot, cover with water.
Place on stove and bring to boil.
When wieners are hot take out of pot and put into buns.

title: old-fashioned peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and soda.
Set aside.
Mix fat and peanut butter.
Add both kinds sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs and mix well. Stir flour mixture into peanut butter mix.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Melt the margarine in a 10-cup refrigerator container, using the microwave oven.
Takes about 1 minute on High.
Add everything else but the flour.
Beat.
Add the flour and mix well. Refrigerate until you are ready to bake muffins.
May bake immediately or wait 2 to 3 days.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix remaining ingredients with broccoli and put into a well greased pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: no bake french cream cake
directions: Place 1 cup crumbs in ungreased 8 inch square pan. Thoroughly cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Spread carefully over crumbs.
Combine cream, nuts and pineapple. Spread over creamed mixture, then sprinkle with remaining crumbs. Let stand 18 to 24 hours in refrigerator.
Cut into squares and serve.
May top with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.
Serves 12 - 16.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew
chicken.	Do
not
salt.	Pick
off bones and put aside. Save
broth.
Melt
margarine
and stir into dressing. In	a greased
dish
x
13-inch), put a layer of dressing crumbs, a layer of chicken, then a layer of mushroom or celery soup (diluted with 1 can of broth).
Again, layer the crumbs, chicken and
can of cream of chicken soup (diluted with 1 can of broth). Top with crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour (or until brown).
Use no salt at all.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix sauce, Accent, cheese and 1 package beef.
Cover and set 24 hours.
Wrap ball with remaining beef and serve.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Put popped popcorn and peanuts in a big roaster or pan.
Put brown sugar, white syrup and oleo in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add soda and immediately pour over popcorn and peanuts.
Put in oven and toss every 15 minutes for 1 hour.
Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: fruited chicken and rice skillet
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken.
Cook and stir 3 minutes. Drain; reduce heat to medium.
Stir in combined dressing, juice and sugar. Add rice and green pepper. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Add oranges and pineapple.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
I also add pea pods.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Cooking time:
10 minutes plus standing. Makes 4 servings.

title: mickey mouse salad
directions: Wash off the lettuce and place on plate.
Lay a pear half on the lettuce.
Cut cherries in half, then place on the end of the pear for a mouth.
Use two raisins for eyes and two pecans for his ears to make a Mickey Mouse face.

title: pot roast
directions: Place roast in large crockpot.
Add all other ingredients. Cook on low 8 hours.

title: sausage balls
directions: Roll into balls and bake at 325° for 12 minutes.

title: french apple cream pie
directions: Put crust in pie pan and fill with apples.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Mix egg, sugar, lemon juice, cream cheese and sour cream.
Mix until smooth.
Pour over sugar and cinnamon apples. Put crust on top and bake in a 425° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook 40-45 minutes at 400 degrees.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Cook 1st four ingredients; stir over medium heat until mixture boils and is bubbling over top. Stir 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add vanilla flavoring and chocolate bits. Stir until melted. Stir in nuts. Spread in buttered pan. Cool thoroughly.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Put bread in the middle of a ball formed around the piece of bread.
Place in boiling water.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve with roast beef, roast pork, etc.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Melt first three ingredients for 2 to 4 minutes on High. Stir.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until soft.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add onions and cook slowly until soft.
Add sugar and salt. Stir and cook one minute.
Boil water and melt bouillon cubes.
Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Add brandy or cooking sherry.
Cook and cover on low 4 to 6 hours. Spoon into soup crocks. Top each crock with toasted French bread.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings. Recipe may be doubled.

title: best yet pineapple cake
directions: Blend together butter, cream cheese, sour cream and sugar. Add undrained pineapple and coconut; blend.
Sprinkle with dry pudding mix as it comes in the package.
Fold in whipped topping. Use to fill and frost layers of yellow cake.

title: diabetic fruit cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to applesauce mixture.
Dough will be thick. Pour into well-greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook vermicelli al dente. Combine all ingredients.
Mix well so that everything is coated. Chill before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Combine dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Add to egg and milk mixture.
Line bottom of a 13 x 9-inch dish with bread.
Cover with sausage.
Pour egg mixture over sausage.
Top with grated cheese.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can freeze up to 6 weeks.

title: sweet and sour venison stew
directions: Brown the venison cubes in the oil in a heavy skillet.
Add the rest of the ingredients (except parsley) and cover.
Simmer for 2 1/2 hours.
Add water during simmering, if needed.
Thicken with instant flour and serve over hot, buttered noodles.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in greased baking dish for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm (leftovers are also good cold).

title: twinkie cake
directions: Slice Twinkies in half and place cream side up in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice bananas on top of Twinkies.
Prepare pudding as per directions and combine with well drained pineapple.
Pour this over bananas.
Next, smooth Cool Whip over top and sprinkle on nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Line spring pan with Lady Fingers.
Melt chocolate in top of double boiler; beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat whites until frothy; add sugar to beaten whites.
In bowl, blend 1/4 of white with chocolate mixture.
Fold in remaining whites.
Fold in Cool Whip and vanilla.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: grilled chicken breasts oriental
directions: Combine all ingredients and set aside for 15 minutes.
Heat grill, charcoal grill or broiler.
Place breasts on hot grill, cooking on each side until done, about 5 to 10 minutes on each side, depending on size of breasts.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Heat
oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and confectioners sugar. Blend
in
flour.
Press evenly in bottom of ungreased pan, 13
x 9
x
2-inches.
Bake
for
12 to 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread over hot, baked layer and bake 20 minutes longer.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: lemon angel food cake
directions: Use the whole egg and prepare pudding as directed on box.
Tear angel food cakes in 1-inch pieces.
Alternate with pudding (layer cakes, then layer pudding) in cake pan.
Put in refrigerator for several hours.
Invert cake in plate after chilling and ice with Cool Whip.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Place beans in a Dutch oven with water.
Bring to a boil; simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour. Drain and rinse beans.
Return to Dutch oven with broth, garlic and bay leaves; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 1/4 hours.
Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until beans and vegetables are tender and gravy is thick.
Remove bay leaves.
Serve over rice.
Makes 12 servings.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: First Layer:
Crush pretzels, add sugar and margarine.
Mix. Spread in 11 x 14-inch Pyrex.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: fresh coconut cake(16 servings)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Grease and lightly flour three 9-inch cake pans.
In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar, using an electric mixer if possible.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
The mixture should be smooth and creamy.
Using a spoon, add one-third of the milk.
Repeat until flour and milk are incorporated.
It is important that ingredients be folded in; batter should not be beaten after flour has been introduced.

Stir in vanilla. Distribute batter evenly among three cake pans and bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 30 minutes, or until layers are golden brown and spring back when gently pressed in the middle. Cool for about 5 minutes and turn layers out of pans.

title: 7-up lemon pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Add flour alternately with lemon extract and 7-Up.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
When thoroughly cool, sift powdered sugar over cake. This cake freezes well and stays moist.
Serves 16.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Line a 10-inch pie plate with crusts.
Defrost vegetables, but do not cook.
Mix milk with soup. Stir vegetables into soup. Pour mixture into crust. Cover with sliced cheese.
Cover with top crust.
Vent.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients in bowl and set aside.
Beat remaining ingredients together until smooth.
Grease tube pan. Put layer of batter, layer of apples several times, ending up with apples on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serves 15 people.

title: pan toasted fish
directions: Place fish in shallow baking dish and cover with milk. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Drain and pat dry.
Combine egg white and lemon juice in a separate shallow dish and set aside.
Combine oat bran, paprika and black pepper.
Dip fillets in egg mixture then oat mixture.
Saut in oil in nonstick skillet 3 minutes on each side or until evenly browned.
Serves 4.

title: ginger-marinated chicken wings
directions: Arrange wings evenly in the bottom of a shallow dish.
Combine soy sauce, honey, arrowroot, vinegar, ginger and garlic in a bowl. Pour marinade evenly over top.
Cover and chill up to 4 hours. Remove wings from marinade.
Arrange on broiler pan.
Cook, turning and basting with the marinade several times for 15 to 20 minutes, or until done to your liking.

title: pecan pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pan with pastry 1/8 inch thick.
Combine ingredients, adding pecans last.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes longer or until a silver knife inserted in center of filling comes out clear.

title: cold chicken curry
directions: Cook rice; refrigerate until cool.
Toss rice, cauliflower and French dressing; cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
In a large bowl, combine the mayonnaise, curry powder, salt and pepper.
Stir in milk.
Add chicken and toss.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
In a large bowl, mix the rice and chicken.
Add green pepper, celery and onion.
Turn on platter lined with romaine leaves.
Top with almonds.

title: sausage soup
directions: Brown and drain sausage and onions.
Combine all ingredients in large pot and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
May be thinned with more broth or water.
May be frozen.

title: shepards pie
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onions.
Cook until onion softens.
Add tomato soup and beans.
In a bowl put mashed potatoes plus eggs (beaten with a fork) and grated cheese.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs with sugar until light and well blended.
Beat in oil.
Sift dry ingredients together; beat into egg mixture.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until cake tests done. Let stand in pan 10 minutes.
Turn onto rack to cool.
Serve with whipped cream or ice with cream cheese icing.

title: easy spicy-sweet chicken
directions: Pound chicken to 1/2-inch thickness; sprinkle with salt to taste.
Cook chicken in oil in 10-inch skillet over medium heat cooked through, about 5 minutes on each side.
Remove from skillet and reserve.
Increase heat to medium-high.
Add picante sauce, marmalade and peas to skillet; mix well.
Cook and stir 3 minutes or until sauce has thickened.
Return chicken to skillet; spoon sauce over chicken and heat through, about 1 minute.
Serve with additional picante sauce, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy sticky cinnamon rolls
directions: Thaw bread dough at room temperature (1 1/2 to 2 hours). Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Tear off bread dough in two-inch balls.
Place in greased pan.
Melt butter and add remaining ingredients.
Pour over balls.
Let rise 2 hours at room temperature.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: dorothy's muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of muffin tins or use paper liners.
Beat egg, melted margarine and milk.
Combine dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Stir until flour is moistened.
Stir in marmalade, mixing well.
Divide equally into 12 prepared muffin tin cups.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook
squash and onions until tender.
Drain well.
Add butter and mix well.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole and top with layer of cracker crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: easy lasagna ii
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine meat and spaghetti sauce.
Mix eggs into cottage cheese.
Spread a thin layer of sauce in pan.
Add a layer of the uncooked lasagne noodles, a layer of the cottage cheese mixture, a layer of cut up Mozzarella and a generous layer of sauce.
Repeat layers, ending with the sauce.
Cover tightly with heavy-duty foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Let stand, covered, outside of oven for 12 to 20 minutes before serving.
Sprinkle with Parmesan before serving.

title: creamy baked chicken breast
directions: Arrange chicken in lightly greased 13 x 9 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Combine soup and wine; stir well.
Spoon evenly over chicken.
Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: rocky road candy
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt morsels with Eagle Brand milk and margarine.
Remove from heat.
In a large bowl, combine nuts and marshmallows; stir in chocolate mixture.
Spread in wax paper lined 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill for 2 hours or until firm.
Remove from pan; peel off paper and cut into squares. Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: four fruit compote
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3/4 cup juice.
In a saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon juice.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly; cook and stir 1 minute longer.
Remove from the heat and set aside.
In a bowl, combine fruit.
Pour warm sauce over the fruit.
Stir gently to coat.
Cover and refrigerate.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: chili dip (a hit)(quick and easy)
directions: Use microwave or conventional oven.
Put Hormel chili in bowl. Cut Velveeta in small chunks.
Place in chili.
Drain chilies and mix with chili and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or microwave until cheese is melted.
Stir frequently.
Dip with nacho chips.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Then add buttermilk, raisins, dates and nuts.
Cream the rest of ingredients together. Mix together all ingredients in large bowl.
Makes about a gallon. Cook in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a large heavy pan, place sugar, oleo and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until ingredients melt. Continue cooking to soft ball stage, 235° on candy thermometer. Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Pour into two 8 x 8 x 2-inch pans (buttered).
Cut into squares when cold.
You may add nuts or use crunchy peanut butter.

title: microwavable rice krispies treats
directions: Put butter into glass, microwavable tray.
Microwave for 30 seconds.
Add marshmallows into tray; microwave 2 to 3 minutes. Add Rice Krispies cereal evenly.
Mix evenly.
Set to cool for 10 minutes.
Cut into squares and enjoy.

title: magic meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potatoes, in large bowl.
Shape into a loaf.
Place in crock-pot.
Place potatoes at the sides of loaf.
(If potatoes are peeled, wrap in foil to keep from darkening.)
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours, on high for 4 to 5 hours.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, brown sugar and egg.
Stir in applesauce.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt and spices and mix well together.
Add nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown in a 375° oven for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fresh and creamy potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, green peppers, onion and salt; mix lightly.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream and milk, mixing until well blended.
Add to potato mixture; mix lightly.
Chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken fried round steak
directions: Pound steak thoroughly.
Cut in serving pieces.
Blend egg and milk.
Dip meat in egg mixture, then in crumbs.
Slowly brown meat in hot oil (iron skillet works well), turning once.
Season with salt and pepper; cover.
Cook over low heat for 30 to 45 minutes or until tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Mix flour, pineapple, 1 1/2 cups sugar and soda.
Pour in ungreased pan.
Cut butter into pats and place on top.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Mix together 3/4 cup sugar, butter, cream and nuts.
Cook slow until thickened.
Pour over cake when cake is done.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add cranberries, then add pineapple, sugar, nuts and oranges.
Jellied cranberry sauce also can be used instead of whole cranberries.
Put into glass dish or mold.

title: chicken and ham party salads
directions: Put chicken through meat grinder (hand operated). Mix with other ingredients in a bowl.

title: pizza omelet(serves 2)
directions: Allow 3 eggs for 2 servings.
For each egg, add 1 tablespoon evaporated milk, 1/8 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Beat eggs slightly; beat in milk and seasonings.
Heat 1 tablespoon butter in heavy skillet and add eggs and cook slowly.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Blend all together except 1 teaspoon soda.
Cook until thick in double boiler; add soda.
Pour puffed up filling in pie shell. Cover with meringue made from the 3 egg whites.
Put in oven to brown.

title: "new moon" tea cakes
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well. Add egg yolks and beat well, about 5 minutes. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together and add in 3 parts to creamed mixture, blending it well. Add vanilla. Clean beaters and beat egg whites in another bowl until stiff, but not dry.
Pour on top of the batter and with spatula or rubber scraper, fold in gently.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Dust with flour.
Pour in batter and spread to corners.
Sprinkle with walnuts and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Lightly dust with powdered sugar while warm. Cool and cut with a serrated round cookie cutter so you will have half moon shaped little cakes.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Mix flour and sour cream.
Add cream of mushroom soup and white wine.
Mix in pepper and garlic salt.
Place chicken breasts into baking dish.
Add mixture onto top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 90 minutes.
If desired, you can then turn onto broil until top is slightly brown.
Served with brown rice is good.

title: cinnamon toast
directions: Heat the oven.
Butter 2 pieces of bread.
Place cinnamon on bread.
Butter the bread.
Cook for about 5 minutes.

title: coconut pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/4 cup water.
Cook next nine ingredients in double boiler or in a microwave until slightly thick (12 to 15 minutes).
Remove from heat and stir in the gelatine; cool.

title: oriental steak broil
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, combine the lemon juice, oil, garlic, soy sauce, salt, pepper and aniseed.
Bring to a boil over high heat and stir about 30 seconds or until the salt dissolves.
Put the steak into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch non-aluminum baking dish and pierce all over with a fork.
Pour the hot marinade over the steak, turn the steak over in the marinade to coat it well and marinate at room temperature for 30 minutes (or longer if you have time), turning once.
Preheat the broiler.
Place the steak on the rack of the broiler pan about 2 or 3 inches from the heat.
Broil for 5 to 7 minutes per side for medium.
Cut the steak on the diagonal into 1/2-inch slices.
Makes 4 servings, 340 calories per serving.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix margarine and flour together and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: berry banana smoothie
directions: Combine ingredients in a blender; cover and blend until smooth. Makes 2 (8 ounce) servings.

title: skillet candied sweet potatoes(serves 6)
directions: Melt butter in a skillet.
Stir in brown sugar, water and salt.
Add sliced potatoes.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat 10 to 15 minutes or until glazed, basting and turning gently 2 or 3 times.

title: cherry-chocolate cups
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture; mix well.
Divide dough in half.
To one half add nuts and chocolate.
Press a rounded teaspoonful of chocolate mixture into the bottom and up sides of ungreased 1 3/4-inch muffin cups.
Place a cherry half in the center of each cup.
Top with a rounded teaspoonful of the remaining white dough and another cherry half. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 32.

title: walnut cheese patties
directions: Mix together and form into patties.
Fry in small amount of oil (not too hot of pan) until golden brown.
Cover with mushroom or onion gravy.
Also can be used with tomato sauce.
These patties can be made up ahead and frozen until ready to use.

title: wall cleaner
directions: Mix together.
Good to wash walls.
This does a good job for pennies.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Sprinkle coconut and chopped nuts in bottom of pan.
Mix together cake mix.
Spread over coconut and nuts.
Mix together confectioners sugar, melted butter and softened cream cheese.
Spread over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix beef, onion, egg, parsley and crumbs.
Form into balls and brown.
Pour off drippings.
Stir in soup, water and pickles. Cover; cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Delicious with any meal.

title: scrumptious minted brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine brownie mix, egg, water and oil in a large bowl.
Stir with spoon until well blended, about 50 strokes.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake for 25 minutes or until set.
Place 30 wafers evenly over hot brownies.
Let stand for 1 minute to melt.
Spread candy wafers to frost brownies.
Score frosting into 36 bars by running tip of knife through melted candy.
Do not cut through brownies. Cut remaining 18 candy wafers in half lengthwise; place halves on each scored bar.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.

title: tuna vegetable souffle
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Prepare 4 servings of potatoes, omitting butter.
Fold in mayonnaise.
Add egg yolks, one at a time; beat until fluffy.
Stir into vegetable mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in.
Pour into greased 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bacon-wrapped mushroom caps
directions: Cut the bacon strips in half and wrap each strip around the perimeter of each mushroom cap to create a small cuff.
Fasten the back with a toothpick.
Broil mushrooms 5 minutes or until the back becomes slightly crisp, drain.
Mix the cheese with onion and bread crumbs.
Place a small mound of mixture inside each mushroom cap within the bacon cuff.
Broil 3 minutes. Serve hot.

title: eye of round roast
directions: Marinate night before.
Bring to room temperature.
Preheat oven to 500° and cook 6 minutes per pound.
Turn oven off and leave for 2 hours without opening door.

title: large cheesecake
directions: Crush graham crackers and mix well with melted butter.
Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla and cream cheese. Beat well.
Put crackers in spring-form pan and pour in cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes. Remove from oven and cool 10 minutes.
Increase oven to 475°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put fruit in large bowl with fruit cocktail juice.
Pour pudding over fruit and mix.

title: deep fried pickles
directions: In a large bowl, combine 2 eggs, 1/4 c. of the flour, buttermilk, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce, cayenne pepper, seasoning salt and garlic powder.
In a separate mixing bowl, combine cornmeal, 2 c. flour, salt and 3/4 tsp. black pepper. Preheat oil in a deep fryer or pot to 365°.
Dip drained pickles into milk mixture and then dredge them in the flour mixture.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Bring cranberries and water to a boil.
Simmer on low heat for 10 minutes.
Allow to cool. add sugar and jello.
Mix well. Add the apple, pineapple and nuts,
mix well. Pour into mold and refrigerate until set or overnight.

title: spicy cole slaw
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in small pan and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Pour the cooled mixture over the prepared vegetables and toss lightly.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight to blend flavors.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and sugar together. Cut in shortening. Add sweet potatoes. Stir in buttermilk. May need more to make stiff dough. Turn onto floured board and knead lightly. Roll out and cut into biscuits. Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: twister pie
directions: Combine Tropicana Twister, Cool Whip and condensed milk.
Beat thoroughly.
Pour into pie crust and chill.
Serves 6.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix together, press and roll into small balls.
Then flatten. Bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Let cool slightly.
Cover in sugar and cinnamon.

title: sand tarts
directions: Add enough flour to the ingredients to make a moderately stiff dough.
Make into a long roll.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill overnight in refrigerator.
Cut off small portions and roll thin. After cutting, brush each cookie with unbeaten egg white.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Trim with candy or nuts.
For other holidays, trim with colored sugar, sprinkles, etc.
They keep well.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Finely grate cheese.
Mix with oleo, flour and pepper.
Place small balls (about size of a quarter) on ungreased cookie sheet. Pat flat with back of fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from pan while still hot.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Butter 10-inch pie plate.
In a saucepan melt 3 tablespoons of butter; add onion and green pepper.
Saute until tender.
Stir in meat; brown.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Add 2 tablespoons butter to cooked spaghetti.

title: coconut shortbread
directions: Cream the sugar and butter together, then stir in remaining ingredients.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill.
to bake, slice in 1/4 inch slices and put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15-20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butters, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Crisscross with fork tines. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: applesauce jello
directions: Melt red hots and sugar into the water.
Add jello and applesauce.
Pour into mold.
Chill several hours.

title: clam chowder
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Season to taste with lemon juice. Simmer until shrimp are tender.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: In a double boiler, mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add lemon juice, orange juice and pineapple juice.
Cook over warm water for 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
Beat eggs and slowly add to cooked mixture.
(It is best to add a little cooked mixture to the eggs and blend well, then return to double boiler.)
Cook, stirring, 5 minutes more.
Cool and blend with cream cheese.

title: dad's favorite cheese ball
directions: Soften the cream cheese.
Mix in Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and Accent to taste.
Chop green tops of onions and dried beef.
Reserve about 1/3 of the chopped dried beef.
Add remaining beef and about an equal portion of green onion tops to cream cheese mixture.
Shape mixture into a ball, then roll in reserved beef.
Serve with crackers (Sociables, Dad's favorite) or vegetables.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Heat chocolate chips, condensed milk and margarine until melted, then add flour, vanilla and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon; add beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients; mix and put into greased loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter surprise cake
directions: Coarsely chop the peanut butter cups into random pieces; spread in a metal pan and freeze solid. Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a 9
x 13-inch pan.

title: overnight tuna casserole(microwave)
directions: Whisk soup and milk in
a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients except 1/4 cup cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours or overnight. Cover with lid or vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 15 to 17 minutes, until bubbly.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Let stand uncovered 5 to 7 minutes until cheese melts.

title: orange roughy de jonghe
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place fillets in a shallow, buttered baking dish (about 7 x 10-inch).
Pour sherry over fillets. Combine mayonnaise, garlic, parsley and bread crumbs.
Spread evenly over fillets.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until fork-tender.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown	hamburger
and	onions	in
frying
pan.
Drain grease.
Salt and pepper hamburger.
Place Tater Tots over the bottom of the casserole dish.
Put hamburger over top of Tater Tots.
Place
remaining Tater Tots over top.
Spoon soups over the top of
the Tater Tots.
Bake in oven for 30 to 45 minutes on 325°.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Mix pudding and milk, then add to first mixture.
Crush package of Oreos, centers included; half goes on bottom, half goes on top.
Chill at least 24 hours before serving.

title: gumbo style okra
directions: Saut chopped onion in melted butter until onions are clear. Stir in remaining ingredients and cook over low heat until okra is tender.
Season with salt and pepper to suit your taste.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and condensed milk in mixing bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Add lemon juice and vanilla; mix.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill for 1 hour.
Pour on pie filling and chill before serving.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pierce cake with fork while hot and pour Eagle Brand over cake.
Set.
Pour Coco Lopez and let set again.
Cool.
Put on Cool Whip; sprinkle with coconut.
Serve cold.

title: veggie mix
directions: Mix sugar, oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and water together and boil until sugar has melted; let cool to warm stage.

title: frozen lemon squares
directions: Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar; press onto 8-inch square pan.
In bowl beat egg yolks.
Stir in condensed milk and lemon juice.
Add yellow food coloring if desired.
Pour into crust. Top with whipped cream or topping and freeze.
Keep cool.

title: bruschetta
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a small bowl.
Let stand so tomatoes release their juices.
Brush both sides of bread with olive oil.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat source on both sides until lightly browned.
Place bread on serving plates and spoon topping over slices.
Serve immediately.

title: small party meatballs
directions: Combine
all
ingredients.
When thoroughly mixed shape into small
balls.
I
use
a
teaspoon
to get uniform size. Place
in baking dish and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serve in barbecue sauce or sweet and sour sauce.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Heat oil.
Saute next 4 ingredients until tender.
Add tomatoes and brown.
Stir in paprika, cayenne, salt and water. Add a bay leaf and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and continue simmering for 10 to 12 minutes.
Thicken sauce with cornstarch mixed with a little cold water.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: yummy breakfast roll
directions: Place 1 can of rolls in bottom of a 9 x 13 pan. Mix 1 cup sugar, cream cheese and vanilla together. Spread over rolls. Spread 2nd can of rolls over cream cheese. Melt butter; mix with 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon. Pour over rolls. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: tortillas (flour)
directions: Sift
flour
and salt together and work shortening into it with hands and fingertips, then add water until dough forms into firm ball.
Knead well and form into small balls the size of golf balls.
Let
stand for about 15 minutes and then roll into thin pancake
size of 7 to 8 inches.
Cook on moderately hot griddle or skillet (ungreased) for 2 minutes on one side; turn over
and cook
1 minute on the other side.
Serve while hot.
(These
can be
placed
in foil and reheated in oven at 350°
for approximately 10 minutes.) Serve with butter spread on them or fill with cooked refried beans, cheese, etc.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach; drain, squeezing out liquid.
Add remaining liquids; mix well.
Chill 2 hours or more in refrigerator, then roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet (can line sheet with heavy Reynolds Wrap for easy cleaning).
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes, shaking the pan for even cooking.

title: sugar 'n spice cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Mix in molasses.
Mix in spices.
Add flour and mix well.
Form into balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: corn-crisped pork chops
directions: Combine corn flake crumbs, Accent, salt and pepper.
Dip chops in evaporated milk, then roll them in crumb mixture.
Place in shallow baking pan, greased and lined with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until meat is tender when pierced with a fork.

title: bread dressing
directions: Saute onion, celery and seasonings in margarine.
Add broth. Add broth to bread crumbs until moistened.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Add 1 stick of the butter, melted, to the crushed graham crackers to form a thin layer crust.

title: mock lasagna
directions: In a baking pan spread 1 can ravioli.
In small bowl combine egg, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Spoon over ravioli.
Top with half the cheese slices.
Spoon remaining ravioli over cheese layer.
Bake uncovered in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese slices.
Bake until cheese melts.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: tuna puffs
directions: Early in the day:
Combine eggs, crumbs, salt, mustard, onions, milk and tuna.
Pour into 6 individual casseroles or 8 custard cups.
Refrigerate.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cut tops off beets; cook until tender.
Peel and cut beets in size wanted.
Boil vinegar and sugar together.
Add cooked beets; bring to boil.
Pack in hot jars; finish filling jar with syrup. Seal; put jars in a 250° oven for 10 minutes.

title: starlight mint surprise cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs, water and vanilla.
Beat well and add flour, salt and baking soda.
Chill dough.
To 1 tablespoon of dough enclose a chocolate star and roll into a ball.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield: 4 1/2 dozen.

title: french dressing
directions: Use equal amounts.
Combine and mix well.

title: jello ice cream
directions: Combine and mix jello, sugar and hot water; add gelatin and ice cream.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan and refrigerate.
It layers by itself.
Cut into desired pieces and serve.

title: civil war pound cake
directions: Dissolve soda (the size of a pea) in 1 tablespoon of cold water.
Beat eggs separately and very well.
Mix whites last.
Fold in carefully.
Bake about one hour or until tested with a straw that comes out clean.

title: german red cabbage
directions: Remove cabbage core; shred cabbage.
Add onion, sugar, salt, bay leaf and water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 20 minutes.
Add vinegar and apple.
Cook additional 3 or 4 minutes.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into lightly greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° until bubbly, usually about 20 minutes.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in butter; drain mushrooms, reserving 3/4 cup of liquid.
Combine eggs, cream, mushrooms and liquid, spices and saltines; add onion and cheese and mix well. Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake covered for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and continue baking for 30 minutes more.

title: ugly dip
directions: Fry sausage, then drain well.
Put both packages of cream cheese and 1 jar of salsa in microwave for about 7 to 10 minutes or until cream cheese begins to melt.	Mix sausage with cream cheese mixture.
Can be served warm or cold with salsa, chips or toast.

title: whole wheat sandwiches with olive filling
directions: Chop almonds until fine; combine with other ingredients.
Trim crust from bread.
Spread one slice with filling.
Top with another slice of bread; cut into finger sandwiches.
Yields 32 sandwiches.

title: instant rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, 2 cups milk, salt, cinnamon, sugar, nutmeg and raisins.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; boil slowly for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Mix eggs with remaining milk.
Slowly add to hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add vanilla. Let cool.
Makes 6 servings.

title: classic green bean casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in green beans and half the onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Stir.
Top with remaining onions. Bake 5 more minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: german style pork chops
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper and bread pork chops, then saute in skillet with butter to slightly brown both sides (1 to 2 minutes). In large pot, add water, soup mix, onion and beer.
Bring to simmer.
Then add breaded pork chops.
Simmer on low for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Thicken with flour or cornstarch and serve over rice or noodles.

title: grannie's peanut butter cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Beat together with sugars, vanilla, peanut butter and eggs.
In a separate bowl, combine the flour, bran, oats and baking soda.
Stir mixture into butter mixture.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool.

title: diabetic snow pudding
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water. Combine lemon juice, rind and boiling water. Bring to boiling point and remove from heat. Add softened gelatin and artificial sweetener. Mix until well dissolved. Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites. Add unbeaten egg whites and extracts. Beat until fluffy and holds shape. Chill until firm

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Sift together flour, brown sugar, baking powder and salt. Add chocolate chips and nuts; toss to coat. Mix egg and oil mixture into dry mix, stirring lightly and quickly, just to mix. Grease bottoms only of muffin tin or use paper baking cups. Fill each cup 2/3 full. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes, until light brown.

title: company chicken
directions: Melt margarine.
With knife, spread sour cream on chicken pieces and roll in crumbs; gently roll chicken in melted margarine (I melt it in a 13 x 9-inch pan) and place in same.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: chicken tinola(chicken papaya)
directions: In saucepan, cook chicken with salt, bagoong or patis and ginger for 20 minutes or until fat collects at bottom of pan. Stir occasionally.
Add water, cover and cook for about 2 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Add papaya cubes and cook for another 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken tostada salad
directions: In small jar, mix vinegar, honey, cumin, salt and pepper. Shake well.
Slice chicken into 1/2-inch strips and toss with garlic salt.
Cook and drain corn.
Add to chicken.
Stir, cover and chill 1/2 hour.
Add tomatoes, beans, onions and lettuce. Toss.
Pour dressing over salad and toss.
At serving time, add cheese and Tostitos and toss gently.
Garnish with salsa and sour cream.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning mix according to instructions.
Let cool.
In a large bowl, mix meat, cheese, onion and tomatoes.
Right before you serve it, add lettuce and crunched Doritos.
Pour dressing over and mix.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Stir in chicken and vegetables. Spread into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix cornflakes, butter and parsley together, then spread it over casserole mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: sensational fish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fish in nonstick baking pan; divide remaining ingredients equally on top of each fillet.
Bake until fish flakes easily when tested with fork, about 15 minutes. Makes 2 servings.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Put pineapple in flat dish.
Mix flour, sugar and cheese and spread over pineapple.
Sprinkle crackers over this, then pour melted margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chops and stuffing
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Place in 12 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Lightly mix bread cubes, onion, butter, 1/4 cup water and poultry seasoning.
Place a mound of stuffing on each chop.
Blend soup and 1/3 cup water.
Pour over stuffing and chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: preacher's coming
directions: Put crushed wafers in ungreased 9 x 13 pan. Melt chocolate in 2/3 cup oleo. Stir in yogurt and 2 beaten egg yolks. Add nuts and vanilla. Fold in egg whites that have been stiffly beaten. Pour over crumbs and chill until firm. Top with 1/2 gallon vanilla ice cream that has been softened. Sprinkle with 1/3 cup nuts. Drizzle with Chocolate Fudge Sauce (follows). Cover and freeze. Cut into squares and serve.

title: chocolate brownie pies
directions: Melt chips with butter, then add other ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Cook in oven at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, jello, vanilla, water, oil and eggs well. Pour mixture into a 10-inch tube pan that has been lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes in the pan.
Mix together the powdered sugar and lemon juice. Drizzle over the cake while it is still warm.

title: none such prize cookies(makes 48 cookies, 3-inches in diameter)
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking soda. Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Cream smooth.
Add mincemeat, broken into small pieces.
Add flour and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, 2-inches apart, on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes.

title: orange mushroom salad
directions: Toss lettuce, orange slices, mushrooms and onions with dressing until well coated.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Top with raisins, if desired.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed.
After coming to a boil, pour cake mix in pudding pan and stir.
Batter will be a little lumpy.
Pour in greased pan.
Sprinkle chips and nuts on top.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and add sugar, salt and spices. Add butter to pulp and add pulp to liquid. Add milk and beat. Pour into pastry-lined pie plate and bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 30 to 40 minutes, until filling is firm.

title: tomato bisque and macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Add large can of tomatoes.
Heat until real hot (not boiling).
Add 1/2 teaspoon of baking soda.
Stir well.
Add milk until desired amount, about 1 quart.
Salt to taste.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together; shape into ball or log.
Roll in chopped walnuts.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in granulated sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir dry ingredients together and fold into pumpkin mixture.
Spread on greased and floured 10 x
15 x 1-inch cookie sheet.
Top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until done when tested.
Turn out on dish towel sprinkled with powdered sugar. Roll towel and cake together.
Cool.
Unroll.

title: cottage cheese dessert(or salad)
directions: Mix together well. Refrigerate. Will be ready to serve within an hour.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine jello, water, pineapple and berries.
When it begins to thicken, add bananas.
When it begins to get firm, combine the cream cheese, Cool Whip or sour cream and sugar.
Pour into large container half of jello mixture.
Add the cream cheese mixture, then the rest of the jello.
Spread the cream cheese with a spatula.

title: corn pudding
directions: Sprinkle flour in eggs and beat thoroughly.
Beat milk in with flour mixture.
Beat everything together and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Corn pudding should be kind of firm; test with knife.
Should be like a custard.

title: italian "hot bath"
directions: Heat oil and butter in microwave on Full power for 3 minutes. Mix garlic and anchovy into a paste.
Add to oil and butter mixture and microwave on Full power for 3 minutes.

title: ronald reagan's favorite macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni in water until tender and drain thoroughly. Stir in beaten egg.
Mix mustard and salt with 1 tablespoon hot water and add to milk.
Add cheese, leaving enough to sprinkle on top.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Add milk; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until custard is set and top is crusty.

title: crustless coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, milk, coconut, butter and vanilla.
Pour into large greased dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375° (glass dish 350°).

title: lite crab dip
directions: Combine yogurt, mayonnaise, cream cheese and seasonings.
Mix well. Then stir in cheese and crab.
Cover and chill for 2 hours. Sprinkle with paprika. Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate kahlua cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, sour cream, eggs, oil and Kahlua.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into well greased Bundt or other pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tests done.

title: english teaballs
directions: Cream butter and confectioners sugar.
Add dry ingredients. Work with hands to mix.
Add nuts.
Chill.
form into balls. Place on lightly greased pan and bake at 400° for 10 minutes. While warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
When cold, roll again in confectioners sugar.
Yields 50 cookies.

title: season's greeting punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, chill and serve.

title: baked ratatouille
directions: Layer all ingredients in 6-quart casserole, pressing down to make firm.
Drizzle olive oil over top layer.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 3 hours with some of the liquids.
Uncover during last hour if soupy.
Mix gently and salt to taste.
Garnish with parsley and tomato slices.

title: ham and swiss pinwheels
directions: Sprinkle flour over work surface.
Turn dough out onto floured surface and roll into a 12-inch square.
Combine mustard and honey in small bowl and brush over dough.
Sprinkle evenly with cheese. Top with ham slices.
Roll up jelly roll fashion, pinching seam to seal (don't seal ends).
Cut roll into 16 slices.
Place slices, cut side down, on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°) for 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes, or until golden.
Serve immediately.
Yields 16.

title: sparkling pink punch
directions: Mix together lemonade, orange juice and water; chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Garnish with orange slices. Serves 25 to 30.

title: catfish creole
directions: Melt butter in wide frying pan over medium heat. Add onion, celery, green pepper and garlic. Cook until soft, about 7 minutes. Add tomatoes and their liquid (break up tomatoes with a spoon), lemon slices, Worcestershire sauce, paprika, bay leaf, salt, thyme and liquid hot sauce.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for about 15 minutes or until sauce is slightly thickened.
Press fish pieces down into sauce.
Cover pan and simmer until fish flakes. Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly; cut in half lengthwise.
Combine salt, vinegar and water.
Heat to boiling.
Pack cucumbers into clean, hot jars.
Add 2 tablespoons dill seed and 3 peppercorns to each jar.
Fill with boiling pickling syrup to within 1/2-inch from top of jar.
Immediately seal and process in boiling water 10 minutes.

title: swinging salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cream cheese and beat until cheese melts.
Fold in prepared Dream Whip, nuts, marshmallows and salad dressing.
Pour in large mold and chill until firm.

title: raisin squares
directions: Cook raisins in 1 cup of water. Set aside.
Mix dry ingredients and add egg and margarine.
Fold in raisins and water into this mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: seafoam frosting
directions: Mix well with spoon, then put in double boiler and beat until it holds peaks.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Mix rice, soups and water in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Dip chicken breasts in melted margarine, then lay on top of the rice. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour covered.
Uncover and bake 15 more minutes or until chicken is brown.
Sprinkle with paprika before baking to help chicken brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order.
Bake 1 1/2 hours. Bake at 350°.

title: fruit punch
directions: In a punch bowl, combine pineapple and apple juices.
Puree undrained strawberries in blender; stir pureed strawberries into pineapple juice mix.
Pour in ginger ale.
Garnish with strawberry slices, lime slices and fresh mint.

title: frozen chocolate dessert
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in top of double boiler; bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook until chocolate and marshmallows are melted.
Remove and set aside to cool.
Combine butter and coconut in a saucepan over medium heat.
Cook, stirring often, until coconut is lightly browned.
Remove from heat and stir in graham cracker crumbs.
Press 3/4 of crumb mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut ice cream crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Arrange half of slices over crust. Pour 1/2 of chocolate mixture over ice cream; then repeat layers.
Combine remaining mixture and pecans over top.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Yields 15 servings.

title: congo squares
directions: Cream together margarine and brown sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift together and add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts.
Spread on greased cookie sheet and bake about 20 minutes at 375°.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: spaghetti with zucchini sauce*
directions: Wash, but do not peel zucchini.
Trim ends and slice lengthwise into quarters and then into 1/2-inch slices.
Heat oil and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add garlic and zucchini.
Cook until zucchini is golden brown; drain on paper towels.
Discard garlic. Season zucchini with salt and pepper.
Boil spaghetti and drain. Place in warmed serving bowl with remaining 2 tablespoons margarine, Ricotta cheese and generous amount of grated cheese. Salt and pepper to taste.
Toss well and serve with zucchini slices on top.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant in bite size pieces.
This should take about 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook at 475° for 4 weeks.
This will serve 3800 people.
If more are expected, add the two rabbits.
Only do this if needed, as most people don't like hare in their stew.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw frozen bread dough in refrigerator overnight.
Roll or pat thawed bread into a rectangle.
Slightly beat egg; spread some on dough layer.
Add pepperoni on top of egg.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Roll up like jelly roll style.
Connect ends or seal ends.
Brush with remaining egg.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Good served warm or cold.
Snack or meal.

title: creamy lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and pulp.
Pour into crust.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cook ground beef and onions together, browning the meat a little.
Add vegetables and water.
Bring to a boil and sprinkle the rice over and bring to rolling boil; cover and let simmer for 1 hour.
Should be cooked in a 6-quart kettle.
Will serve 6 to 8 people.
Can be served with shredded cheese on top.
This is a good-for-you, low-fat meal.

title: carameled nuts
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cinnamon and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until a soft ball forms when in cold water.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and 2 to 3 cups English walnuts or pecans.
Spread out and cool.

title: sharon's toffee
directions: Soft boil until golden brown.
(Can add nuts and pecans.) Use heavy pan.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pat into a 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 400° 5 to 7 minutes. Cool 1 hour.

title: seven up salad
directions: Combine jello with hot water.
Add cream cheese and beat with beater until fairly smooth.
Add rest of ingredients and beat. Chill until solid.

title: george washington's cherry tree cake(make this in honor of his birthday or someone else's!)
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking soda and cinnamon and add to first mixture.
Stir in pie filling and chocolate chips.
Pour in two greased and floured cake pans or a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
You can frost if you like.
A rich and moist cake.

title: three cheese and chicken bake
directions: Saute the green pepper and onion in butter. Stir in soup, milk, mushrooms, pimento and basil.
Place half the noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Cover with 1/2 each mushroom sauce, cottage cheese, chicken and cheeses.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients. Add the remaining ingredients and mix well. Cover and refrigerate for 3 hours.
Heat oven to 375°. Shape dough into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place about 3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 2 minutes. Remove from cookie sheet. Makes about 3 dozen. Contains 80 calories per cookie.

title: spiced pecan halves
directions: Beat
egg white and cold water until frothy.
Add pecan halves and
stir to coat evenly.
Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Add coated nuts and stir to coat thoroughly with sugar
mixture.
Place on buttered cookie sheet and bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: beef cabbage soup
directions: Brown ground beef in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add cabbage, celery and onion in skillet.
Transfer to 5-quart stock pot.
Add remaining ingredients, plus 1 cup water, if needed.
Stir and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit soup
directions: Soak the dried fruits in the fruit juice for 2 hours or longer; add 2 teaspoons honey.
Bring mixture to a boil; add cornstarch and stir until mixture begins to thicken.
Add cinnamon; chill or serve warm.

title: hot rib sauce
directions: If
you use pork or have much grease
from cooked meat, use a tablespoon of lemon juice also.

title: mottogany wings
directions: Bake wings at 350° for 20 minutes.
Drain any liquid from pan. Combine soy sauce and brown sugar.
Pour over drained wings. Continue baking for 35 to 40 minutes, until wings are glazed. Serve hot by keeping in a crock-pot or warmer.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter in a skillet.
Add scallops and spices; cook over low heat 8 to 10 minutes.
Blend in the flour; add warmed cream.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until it comes to a boil.
Remove and pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt remaining butter in small saucepan; add crumbled crackers and stir.
Sprinkle cracker mixture over the top of casserole.
Bake, covered, at 425° for 10 minutes.
Uncover; bake an additional 5 minutes.
Let cool for a few minutes before serving.

title: honey lemon chicken
directions: Combine first five ingredients in shallow baking dish.
Stir until well blended.
Place chicken in marinade.
Turn to coat. Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Turn once.
Heat broiler or prepare grill 3 to 5 minutes per side.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baptist chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender (leave skin on).
Debone and set aside.
Butter baking dish.
Prepare Stove Top as directed on package.
Layer in bottom of pan.
Put chicken on top of stuffing. Mix cream of chicken soup with chicken broth.
Pour over layers. Bake, covered, for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: floreeta's angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/3 cup lukewarm water.
Mix dry ingredients.
Cut into shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast to dry ingredients (batter will not be stiff).
Let stand at room temperature about 20 minutes.
At this point, batter may be refrigerated for several days.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter.
Add sugars and cream. Add eggs and vinegar; mix well.
In separate bowl, combine flour, oats, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add a little at a time to creamed mixture until well blended.
Add chocolate chips, candy bar and nuts.
Roll into balls.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Use large flat serving dish. Spread bean dip on dish. Mash together avocados with lemon juice and spread on beans. Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and seasoning. Spread on avocado layer. Top with chopped vegetables and cover with cheese. Serve with corn chips.

title: baked shoestring potatoes
directions: Cut a 24-inch length of heavy-duty aluminum foil. Cut potatoes in thin lengthwise strips as for French fries and place just off center on foil. Dot with butter. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, cheese and parsley.
Pull edges of foil upward, then pour cream over the potatoes.
Fold foil.
Place on shallow pan and bake in very hot oven at 450° about 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done. Fold back edges of foil and sprinkle potatoes with extra chopped parsley, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in a pan on stove.
Let come to a boil and let boil for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, then put in vanilla flavoring.
Add peanut butter and then you add your oatmeal, a little at a time.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper. Cool and enjoy!!

title: lemon tarts
directions: Mix all the ingredients (except pie shells and coconut), adding lemon juice last.
Bake pie shells; cool.
Put in cooled pie shells and sprinkle with coconut.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Heat butter until hot; add onion and mushrooms.
Saute until light brown.
Sprinkle flour over onions and mushrooms; stir quickly.
Add milk gradually; stir constantly and bring to boil. Reduce heat; let simmer until mixture thickens.
Stir in remaining ingredients and cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve on toast.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Place vegetables and broth in saucepan.
Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and cook until vegetables are tender, about 8 minutes. Mix milk, cornstarch, salt, pepper and thyme; add to cooked vegetables.
Cook, stirring constantly, until soup is slightly thick and mixture just begins to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Makes 4 servings, 1 cup each.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt Milky Ways and add one stick margarine.
Set aside. Cream one stick margarine with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Add flour and buttermilk to which soda and vanilla have been added and chopped nuts.
Bake in tube or oblong pan 1 hour at 300°.

title: honey wheat bread
directions: Heat milk, butter, cottage cheese and honey until butter melts.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix whole wheat flour, sugar and salt.
Beat the eggs and add to liquid ingredients.
Add this to dry ingredients and mix well.
Add enough white flour to form a ball (2 to 3 cups).
Knead 10 minutes. Let rise in a greased bowl.
Punch down and divide in 2 or 3 parts.
Cover and let rest for 10 minutes.
Form into loaves and let rise.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning into refried beans.
Spread into small casserole dish.
Spoon sour cream on top of and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave on High for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine, eggs, sugar and vanilla until fluffy. Add sour milk, flour and cocoa. Beat. Add hot water and soda. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: whole wheat pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and cream together. Add eggs,
one
at
a time, and beat.
In a separate bowl sift together whole wheat flour, all-purpose flour and salt; add to sugar
mixture.
Add vanilla and milk.
Mix well and pour into greased and
floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: tandoori chicken
directions: Skin chicken.
Slash chicken flesh.
Combine ingredients in bowl.
Add chicken, turning to coat.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Let chicken stand 1 hour at room temperature before cooking.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Arrange in shallow baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes; turn and coat with marinade.
Bake until chicken is fork-tender.

title: tasty tidbits
directions: Melt margarine.
Add seasoning.
Mix well.
Add cereal, nuts and pretzels.
Toss to mix.
Bake 250° 1 hour. Stir often cool and store in airtight jars.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour into pan on top of melted oleo.
Add peaches on top of this.
Add remaining sugar over this.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Chill overnight. Serve with fresh chilled vegetables.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed on the box.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Mix remaining ingredients and toss together until the macaroni is well coated.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup hot water. Makes 125 cups.
Stores very well in a tight container.

title: crazy cake
directions: Add all ingredients in 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Mix with fork. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple raspberry punch
directions: Pour pineapple juice and ginger ale over vanilla ice cream and raspberry sherbet until melted and blended.
Makes 24 (4-ounce) servings.

title: baked apricot casserole
directions: Butter a shallow casserole.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add juice of 1 to 1 1/2 cans of apricot juice, flour and brown sugar. Stir until thickened.
Arrange apricots in dish.
Pour sauce over fruit.
Crumble crackers on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (approximately 25 to 30 minutes).

title: fettucine with ham and peas
directions: Saute the garlic in 1 tablespoon oleo. Stir in ham and peas. Saute 3 to 5 minutes. Remove from heat, cover and keep warm.
Cook the fettucine, omitting the salt. Drain well and place in a large serving bowl.
Add 1/2 cup oleo.
Stir until melted.
Add cheese and sour cream. Stir gently.
Fold in ham mixture and pepper. Toss gently. Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: fluffy coconut pudding
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Cool to room temperature.
Beat egg whites with salt until frothy.
Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Continue beating until mixture holds a peak when beater is lifted.
Slowly beat gelatin.
Add vanilla to whipped cream.
Mix and fold into egg whites.
Fold in coconut. Cover and chill at least 4 hours.
Garnish with Mandarin oranges and serve.

title: potato soup
directions: In a pot, add potatoes and onion to boiling water.
Cover; cook 15 to 20 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Blend in milks, butter and seasonings.
Cook until heated.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the 2 sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and baking soda, salt and water.
Mix well.
Add chocolate chips. One cup of chopped nuts may be added, if desired.
Drop by 1 round teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serves 36.

title: traveling taco dip
directions: Spread beans over bottom of 10-inch glass pie plate.
Layer remaining ingredients in the order listed.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 8 servings.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Sift flour.
Measure and add sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon. Sift again.
Work the shortening into this mixture as for pastry. Stir in chopped nuts and raisins that have been dusted with flour. Add ground apples and stir only enough to blend ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 4 x 8 x 3 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Yield:
one loaf.

title: sausage pie
directions: Set oven to 375°.
Mix all together and fill pie shell.
Bake 1 1/4 hour.

title: cream puff pastry
directions: Combine water and butter in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Add flour and salt to butter mixture.
Stir vigorously until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a ball.
Let cool 4 to 5 minutes. Add eggs one at a time, beating with wooden spoon after each addition.
Spoon dough into mound on baking sheet and bake as directed.
Cut tops off and pull out soft dough inside.
Fill with cream filling.

title: indulgence chocolate mousse
directions: Heat the milk and chocolate over low heat. Stir until melted. Remove from heat. Beat yolks and vanilla together, then add the chocolate mixture. Return to heat and stir until thick. Beat the egg whites to stiff peaks and fold gently into the chocolate mixture. Divide into cups and refrigerate until firm.
This is only 129 calories per serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: rolled buttermilk dumplings
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt.
Add buttermilk and mix lightly with a fork.
Turn out on a floured board or pastry cloth.
Knead lightly 4 or 5 times.
