Roll or pat out to 1/4-inch thick; cut into rectangles 1 x 3-inch with a floured knife.
Drop into boiling stew.
Cover and boil gently 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not uncover while cooking.

title: coolest banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk in a large bowl. Stir in whipped topping, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Layer 1/3 each of the wafers, pudding mixture, bananas and berries in serving bowl. Repeat layers twice. Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Makes 12 servings.

title: homemade coconut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Melt butter and pour into ingredients.
Bake at 350°.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Form into small balls and place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve in brown gravy.

title: best ever fudge
directions: Melt butter with the cheese.
Sift together cocoa and powdered sugar and add to cheese mixture, then add vanilla and nuts to taste.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and slice.
Very creamy.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Spread rolls out and blend seams together in a large rectangle cake pan.
Bake 10 minutes or less.
(Check at 8 minutes according to package directions.)
Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and salad dressing together and spread on top of baked crust.
Garnish with chopped fresh broccoli, cauliflower, tomato, peppers, onion (whatever you like, or is in season).
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over this.
Cut into bars.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: ole fashioned beet pickles
directions: Wash fresh beets and leave an inch of the top stems so the juice will not cook out so much.
I sort the beets according to size and this eliminates overcooking of small beets.
Save a few cups of the red water the beets were cooked in.
Beets are tender when tested with a fork.
Drain off the hot water and cover with cold water until cool enough to handle.
Peel beets and cut off the stems.
Leave small ones whole, but large beets still need to be quartered.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly the first 6 ingredients. Blend in flour and salt.
Divide dough in half; blend food coloring into 1/2.
Shape 1 teaspoon dough from each 1/2 into 4-inch rope. Roll back and forth on lightly floured board.
Place ropes, side by side.
Press together lightly and twist.
Place on ungreased baking sheet; curve top of cookie to form a cane.
Bake about 9 minutes, until set and very light brown.
Makes about 2 to 4 dozen cookies, depending on size of canes.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda together; set aside. Cream butter and sugar in separate bowl.
Add eggs to creamed mixture, one at a time.
Add milk and flour mixture.
Mix well. Fold in nuts, dates and cherries.

title: caramel pull-a-parts
directions: In Bundt
pan
or angel food cake pan, sprinkle nuts on bottom.
Place
frozen
dough
balls
side	by
side in single layer.
Melt
margarine
or
butter;
mix in pudding and brown sugar.
Cook
until
sugar	dissolves.
Remove from heat; pour over dough	balls
evenly.	Cover with waxed paper and a towel overnight.	Next
morning,	bake
at
350° for 35 minutes.	To keep rolls	from
burning on top or becoming too crusty, place foil on top
for the first 25 minutes, then remove and bake 10 minutes more.
Turn out on platter while still hot and serve.

title: gloria's lemon squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: confirmation auction cavatini
directions: Brown sausage in skillet. Cook noodles separately until tender. Drain noodles. Mix sausage, noodles and spaghetti sauce in a casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake until melted.

title: white christmas candy
directions: Melt chocolate over medium-low heat, stirring until smooth. Remove from heat. Stir in peppermint crunch.
Spread on parchment paper lined cookie sheets.
Chill in refrigerator 8 to 10 minutes. Break into small pieces.
Store in airtight containers.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds of candy.

title: onion butter
directions: Blend Lipton onion soup mix thoroughly with softened butter. Makes about 1 1/4 cups. Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add enough cold water to reserved liquid to make 1 3/4 cups.
Add to jello; chill until slightly thickened.
Add oranges.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart ring mold.
Chill until firm.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix sugar, water and instant coffee well.
Simmer for one hour. Cool slightly.
Add vodka and vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour into dark bottles and cap.
Keep in cool dark place.
Delicious.
May use the same day made.
Best when allowed to mellow for few weeks.
Need 2 to 3 bottles.

title: honey 'n spice barbecue chicken
directions: Combine Heinz 57 sauce and honey.
Place chicken pieces on broiler or grill; brush with melted butter.
Broil or grill until chicken is tender, turning and basting frequently with sauce. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: coconut crunch
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch baking sheet with Pam; set aside.
Pour entire contents of Eagle Brand milk into a shallow dish.
Cut slices of loaf bread in half and dip into Eagle Brand milk.
Place on the baking sheet and sprinkle each slice with coconut.
Place on lower rack and broil until coconut is lightly toasted.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Place in mixing bowl the water, oats and margarine.
Cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and bake in a pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sweet onion corn bake
directions: In a large skillet, saute onions in butter until tender. In a small bowl, combine the sour cream, milk, dill and salt until blended. Stir in 1 cup of cheese. Stir into the onion mixture; remove from the heat and set aside.

title: salmon steaks with herbed lemon butter
directions: Combine all ingredients but salmon, oil and lemon.
On wax paper, shape mixture into 1 x 7-inch roll. Wrap and chill.
Brush salmon with oil. Barbecue, grill or broil 4-inches from heat 4 to 6 minutes on each side or until fish flakes when tested with a fork.
To serve, top salmon with 1 teaspoon each of the margarine and garnish with lemon wedges and parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings. Equals:
4 protein exchanges, 1/2 fat exchange plus herbed margarine (1 teaspoon = 1/2 fat).

title: potato casserole
directions: Rub each beet with olive oil for added flavor.

title: wanna's peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk; boil until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oleo.
Beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour into a buttered dish; cut when cooled.
This is my secret recipe.
It's yummy!

title: corned beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients well and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: football stew
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 250° for about 6 hours.
Yields 4 servings.

title: quick banana pudding
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until smooth and thickened.
Fold in Cool Whip thoroughly.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding.

title: french dressing
directions: Beat well to blend.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook onion in butter until onion is tender.
Stir in salt, flour and pepper.
Add milk all at once; stir until thick and bubbly.
Stir in broccoli and cheese; cook until cheese is melted.
Cook broccoli until tender before adding to mixture.

title: favas
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add water and 1/4 cup ketchup.
Stir and simmer, then add more water if needed.
Add pepper, parsley, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add another 1/4 cup ketchup and favas with juice.
Simmer about 5 more minutes. Enjoy!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish. Set aside.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and spoon into tortillas; roll up.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan (use about half of mixture).
Spread remaining mixture over all tortillas.
Sprinkle cheeses over top and bake at 350° until bubbly and cheeses melt.

title: bachelor's roast
directions: Rub roast with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Sear roast on all sides in oil.
Remove from pan; drain off excess fat and place in foil lined pan.
Pour Coke and catsup over roast.
Cover loosely with foil and bake 3 hours at 325°.
This is good chopped up and mixed with sauce for barbecue sandwiches.

title: baked beans with hamburger
directions: Saute onion and pepper in a little oil on low heat.
Increase heat and add hamburger.
Mix vinegar, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
After hamburger is browned, add this mixture and onion to it and boil.
Add beans.
Put in a casserole dish and bake 20 minutes at 300°.

title: vegetable pizza(lo-fat)
directions: Several hours ahead:
Combine softened cream cheese and mayonnaise in a medium-size bowl; stir until smooth.
Add the dressing mix; blend well.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

title: hearty cheese ball
directions: Mix with hand forming a ball.
If it comes too soft, refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll lightly in walnut mixture.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: funnel cakes
directions: In a deep bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix eggs and milk together and pour into dry ingredients. Stir with a whisk until batter is smooth.
Pour shortening into a heavy skillet to the depth of 1/2 to 2 inches.
Heat until hot, but not smoking.
Hold a funnel with a 1/2-inch opening in your hand and keep one finger over funnel end.
Hold funnel over hot oil; remove finger from spout.
Using a slow, swirling motion, dribble batter into center of pan.
Let brown on both sides. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: food for fido(for the dog lover)
directions: Mix well and watch tails wag.

title: freezer chips
directions: Slice all vegetables thinly.
Leave skin on cukes.
Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate and stir each day for 5 days. Freeze with liquid for storing.

title: rice consomme
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add rice and mushrooms; simmer for 20 minutes.
Add consomme, water and oregano; stir until well blended.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour (covered).

title: easy summer lemon pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemonade.
Fold in Cool Whip until smooth and well blended.
(Makes two 8-inch pies.) Freeze for about 1 hour before serving.
Store in freezer, well covered.

title: creepy jigglers
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatins in large bowl 3 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate at least 3 hours or until firm.
Dip bottom of pan in warm water about 15 seconds.
Cut into Halloween shapes with cookie cutters all the way through gelatin.
Lift from pan.
Makes 24 pieces.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies finely.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip. Mix milk and instant pudding.
Combine cheese mix and pudding. Layer flowerpot alternately, ending with cookies on top.
Place worms around on top and stick down in the mix.
Add a silk flower in the middle, giving the effect of a pot plant.

title: pear salad
directions: Heat 1 cup pear juice to boiling; mix with Jell-O. Refrigerate and let set until jelled around edges.
Blend cream cheese, salad dressing and mashed pears.
Prepare Dream Whip as directed.
Fold into cream cheese mixture, then fold in Jell-O. Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: banana split(sugar-free torte)
directions: Crush graham crackers. Add melted margarine and mix.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Slice bananas on top. Cook pudding according to directions. Stir in pineapple.
Pour over bananas. Spread 2 cups Cool Whip on top. Refrigerate. Top with strawberries.

title: rabbit baked in mustard, garlic and cream
directions: Coat rabbit pieces with mustard.

Mix minced garlic, pastry and tarragon with a little salt and sprinkle half over the rabbit. Combine the vinegar and broth and pour into a large baking dish. Sprinkle the remaining garlic, minced parsley and tarragon over, then put the rabbit pieces on top.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the potatoes, granulated sugar, milk, eggs and 1/2 cup butter together and place in a greased casserole. Combine the remaining ingredients together and pour on top of potato mixture. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: yummy stuff
directions: Cook pasta in water seasoned with bouillon; drain.
Return to pan; add cheese slice.
Cover, let cheese melt.
Mix in meat and vegetables.
Serve with catsup.

title: melt-away pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks well; combine with sour cream. Sift dry ingredients together; stir into egg yolk mixture. Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in. Drop by large spoonfuls onto hot griddle until tops are bubbly; turn and brown on other side. Makes 10 pancakes.

title: daddy's grilled chicken
directions: The night before, prepare chicken as follows:
Spray chicken with Pam.
Then coat chicken with seasoning salt completely.
Do not add salt or pepper.
Place chicken in a large bowl or platter and cover tightly with foil. Chill overnight.

title: chinese torture
directions: Combine candied ginger, walnuts, syrup, crumbs and melted chocolate.
Form 1-inch balls.
Mix cocoa and sugar.
Coat each ball completely with this mixture.
Wrap and store in refrigerator.

title: meringue cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Beat egg whites to soft peaks. Gradually beat in 1 cup sugar. Beat until stiff. Fold in 1 teaspoon vanilla. Set aside.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Break spaghetti into 3-inch lengths. Cook in a large amount of boiling water; drain.
In Dutch oven or kettle, cook meat, onion and green pepper until meat is browned.
Sprinkle with salt. Gradually stir in soups, milk and 2 cups of the cheese.
Divide spaghetti evenly between two 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dishes.
Into each pan, stir half the soup-meat mixture.
Sprinkle 1 cup cheese atop each dish or use 1 large baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until hot through.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Butter bread lightly.
Arrange corned beef on 4 slices of bread.
Add sauerkraut.
One tablespoon salad dressing.
One slice swiss cheese.
Brown on grill on one side.
Butter other slice of bread and flip and brown on other side.
When cheese is melted. Serve.

title: southwestern grilled cheese sandwiches
directions: Spread 1 side of half the bread slices to taste with chipotles, if using.
Arrange half the cheese slices evenly on top of chipotles.
Scatter green chilies on top, then add remaining cheese and bread.

title: boiled custard
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Add milk, vanilla and nutmeg. Dot with butter.
Pour in pan, place in oven and bake 30 minutes or until set.

title: rich cocoa fudge
directions: Butter an 8 or 9-inch square pan with foil; set aside.
In heavy 4-quart saucepan, stir together the sugar, cocoa and salt. Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to full rolling boil.
Boil, without stirring, to 234° or until syrup forms soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cool at room temperature to 110° (lukewarm).
Beat with wooden spoon until fudge loses its gloss.
Spread in pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch. Slowly add and stir in beet juice and vinegar. Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens and clears.
Add drained beets. Stir to mix.
Let stand 2 minutes to heat the beets through.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream the eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin together.
Sift the other ingredients together and add alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Pour into 3 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: soft shapes
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Mix in sugar and knead until blended.
Divide mixture in half and color one red and green. Shape mixture into 1-inch balls and press nut half into center of each.
Store in airtight container.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Saute the sausage and mushroom stems, garlic and parsley. Drain well.
Add cheese.
Stuff the mushroom caps.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel and slice eggplant very thin.
Dip in egg and Italian bread crumbs.
Fry in olive oil and drain.
Make a sauce with tomato sauce, Romano cheese, salt and pepper, basil, oregano, onion, garlic, Parmesan cheese and mushrooms.
In casserole dish, alternate sauce, eggplant, and Mozzarella cheese (like a lasagna). Bake at 350° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shera jello mold
directions: Mix gelatin with water until dissolved.
Chill until thick but not completely set.
Whip until frosty and light.
Add sour cream and mix well. Chill.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into baking dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: potato salad for 100
directions: Cover potatoes with water; bring to a boil.
Add 1/4 cup salt. Cover and cook until tender.
Drain well; cool slightly.
Combine onions, oil, salt and pepper.
Add to potatoes.
Combine celery, eggs, relish, pimientos, salad dressing and mustard to potato mixture.
Mix lightly but thoroughly to coat potatoes.

title: window washing solution
directions: *BLKLIN sweatshirt.
Cut off the hood with the strings still attached and tie it onto a mop.
Use it to dust ceilings and walls.
The hood can be washed and used over and over again.

title: hunter's stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces.
Add the brown gravy and bake at 465° for about 4 weeks.
Salt and pepper to taste.
This will serve 3,800 people.
If more are expected, the rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary, as most people do not like to find "hare" in their stew.

title: mom's dumplings for chicken and dumplings
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in Crisco shortening.
Stir in just enough milk to make a real thick, sticky dough.
Roll out pretty thin on a floured surface.
Cut into squares.
Drop into boiling broth.
(Scatter your droppings so they don't all goo up.
You can judge this by dropping according to where the boiling bubbles are.)
Cook about 20 minutes.
DO NOT STIR TOO MUCH (just enough to keep the dumplings from sticking to the bottom, otherwise you will break up the dumplings).
Thicken broth with a mixture of flour and milk to desired consistency.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine vanilla wafer crumbs, sugar, cocoa and pecans.
Mix well.
Combine Karo syrup and rum and pour over crumb mixture. Mix well.
Shape into balls and roll in coconut.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: dirt cups(great for kids)
directions: You will need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) plastic cups.
Suggested decorations: gummy worms and frogs, candy flowers, chopped nuts.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Pour undiluted soup in pan.
Combine other ingredients. Cover; heat and serve piping hot on toast.

title: crunchy graham crackers
directions: Place crackers on foil covered cookie sheet.
Melt butter, margarine and sugar.
Bring to boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Pour mixture over crackers and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Break apart.

title: jim's favorite chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa, egg yolks, milk, margarine and vanilla.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour into pie shell. Top with stiffly beaten egg whites, sweetened to taste.
Add cream of tartar to thicken.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Cook on High for 2 minutes. Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together by hand the cake mix, 2 eggs and melted butter. Pat into a well-greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Set aside, then mix 2 eggs, 1 box powdered sugar and cream cheese until well blended.
Pour over cake mixture.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven, let cool and sprinkle with 1/4 cup powdered sugar.

title: nadine's favorite icebox salad
directions: Combine
the
sugar
and
pineapple;
bring
to a boil. Dissolve
gelatin
in water.
Add sugar and pineapple mixture. Put in	refrigerator
until it begins to set, then add cheese, pecans and whipped cream.	Return to refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon and vanilla.
Pour into crust. Chill 3 hours.
Top with your desired amount of pie filling.

title: dieter's swiss mocha
directions: Blend in blender.
Use heaping teaspoonfuls per cup boiling water.

title: special pumpkin soup
directions: Dry bread crumbs in oven at 300° for 15 minutes.
Cut a lid in pumpkin.
Remove seeds and fibrous insides; discard.
Rub inside of pumpkin with mixture of 1 tablespoon butter and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cook onions in 6 tablespoons butter for 10 minutes.
Stir in bread crumbs; continue stirring and cook for 10 minutes longer. Stir in 1/2 teaspoon salt, other seasonings and cheese.
Put crumbs and cheese in pumpkin.
Fill pumpkin with enough chicken broth to fill within 1/2-inch of top.
Put pumpkin lid on.

title: chicken stew with parsley dumplings
directions: Heat chicken, 4 cups of water, onion, bouillon and pepper to boiling in Dutch oven and reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Add carrots and simmer 10 minutes.
Mix flour and 1/2 cup water. Stir flour mixture and celery into chicken. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Combine Bisquick, milk and parsley.
Drop by spoonfuls onto boiling stew. Cook, uncovered, over low heat 10 minutes.
Cover and cook an additional 10 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: bacon appetizers
directions: Cut bacon in 4ths and wrap each piece around a water chestnut. Fasten with toothpick.
Bake on rack at 400° for about 10 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
Pour off grease; put roll-ups into baking dish.
Mix catsup and sugar; pour over rolls and return to oven for about 10 more minutes.
Makes about 50 and may be served hot or cold.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Divide dough and roll out on floured table until 1/4 inch in depth.
Spread with melted butter, Land of Lakes is best, and sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon to cover.
Roll dough up and cut into 3/4 inch slices or larger if desired.
Place on a buttered pan, butter tops and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes, or golden brown.
Take out immediately and invert on another pan.

title: creamed tomatoes
directions: Mash tomatoes in a pan.
Add flour, milk and sugar.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Heat until thick and creamy.
Serve over biscuits.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Combine ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: sweet cinnamon bread
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Grease and flour the bottom only of a 9 x 3-inch loaf pan. Pour batter into pan.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk. Stir in Cool Whip.

In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer graham crackers, 1/2 pudding mixture, layer of graham crackers, other 1/2 of pudding mixture and graham crackers. Spread the chocolate fudge icing over top layer of graham crackers.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: turkey scalloppine
directions: Skin turkey, slice meat across grain, as thin as possible. Salt and pepper slices, coat with flour.
Heat oil and butter in large skillet.
Lightly brown slices, a few at a time, pour off fat, return meat to skillet.
Add Marsala, thyme and oregano; cook until almost dry, turning slices gently as they cook (about 10 minutes).
Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter, add to turkey. Add beef broth.
Cook turkey over gentle heat until almost dry. Beat egg yolk with cream, remove skillet from heat.
Pour cream mixture over turkey slices, turn gently to glaze.
Makes 6 servings.

title: scallop kabobs
directions: Set oven control at broil and/or 550°.
Broil kabobs 3 inches from heat 5 to 8 minutes, turning once and basting with butter.

title: candle stick salad(for holiday dinner party)
directions: *Note:
The number 8 is variable, depending on how many you're having for dinner.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix the jello and the hot water together.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Let stand until well congealed in refrigerator. This is very good and it is very filling.

title: corned beef hash
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Mixture will be sloppy.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until firm and crusty.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat together sugar, oil and eggs.
Add pumpkin and mix well. Sift together flour, baking powder, cloves, salt, baking soda, nutmeg, allspice and cinnamon; mix with first 4 ingredients.
Then add walnuts and raisins.
Bake in 4 loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour (metal pans, 50 minutes).

title: bill's quiche
directions: Pour into crust and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage in skillet; drain.
Cut into small pieces.
Add onion to skillet and cook until soft.
Combine onion with sausage and sprinkle over bottom of pastry shell.
Sprinkle on cheese. Combine egg, salt, light cream and milk.
Beat slightly.
Pour over ingredients in pastry shell.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak, salt and pepper, then add onions and mushrooms. Cook 5 minutes. Add broth and simmer for 45 to 60 minutes or until tender. Blend sour cream and 2 tablespoons flour together. Stir in broth. Cook and stir constantly until thickened and serve over rice or noodles.

title: mother's pecan pie
directions: Turn oven on to 400°.
Put pie into oven, then turn down to 350°.
Place a sheet of foil on top, then bake until center is firm.

title: dandy candy
directions: Combine peanut butter, milk powder, honey and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Next, mix ingredients with spoon.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, stir in sugar, salt, shortening and egg. Mix flour in until dough is easy to handle. No kneading necessary. Grease top of dough and put in refrigerator before using. Shape about 2 hours before serving. Bake at 400 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: For brine, bring first 3 ingredients to boil.
In cold water, wash about 30 (4-inch) pickling cucumbers.
Pack in quart jars. Add spices to each quart jar.
Pour hot brine over cucumbers to within 1/2-inch of top.
Immediately adjust covers.
Process 20 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes about 6 quarts.

title: peach crisp
directions: Place peach slices in an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Cream the butter and 3/4 cup sugar. Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Spoon mixture over fruit. Sift together 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and nutmeg.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour water over top.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: peter pan cookies
directions: Combine margarine, salt and peanut butter; mix well.
Add sugars gradually and cream.
Add eggs and milk; mix well.
Add flour and soda.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Press top lightly with fork to flatten slightly.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: sour cream coconut frosting filling for layers
directions: Mix sugar, sour cream and coconut. Let stand while making layers.
Put between cake layers and refrigerate or mix together overnight. Put between layers next day.

title: batter rolls
directions: Scald milk; stir
in
sugar,
salt
and
oleo.	Cool to lukewarm. Measure warm
water into large bowl.
Crumble yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture, egg (beaten) and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth; stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft
dough.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk,
about 30 minutes.	Punch down and shape into 2 dozen rolls.
Place
on
greased
baking
cake
pans or muffin cups.
Cover.
Let	rise in warm place until doubled in bulk, about 30 minutes.
Bake
in
hot
oven
at 400° about 15 minutes or so.

title: cranberry salad squares
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in whole cranberry sauce and ginger ale.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill until firm. Cut into squares.
Place on lettuce leaf; garnish with sour cream, mixed with a dash of cinnamon.

title: sugar and spice pecans
directions: Boil
all
ingredients	(except
pecans) to a soft ball stage (230°).
Let
cool	a few minutes and stir until mixture begins to look
creamy, then add pecan halves.
Mix well with wooden spoon. When
hard,
turn	out on an oiled sheet or wax paper and break apart.

title: irish potatoes
directions: In medium size mixing bowl mash the hot pulp of baked potato with a fork.
Add the sugar and blend well.
(If the pulp is not hot enough to melt sugar, place bowl in larger bowl with hot water.)
Add vanilla and coconut; work into mixture thoroughly. Form dough into small rounds and roll each one in cinnamon lightly.

title: southwest beans
directions: Brown beef and onion in oil.
Stir in flour and add seasonings.
Add tomato sauce and 2 cups of the liquid the beans were cooked in.
Simmer about 45 minutes.
Add beans and simmer until flavors blend.

title: one-step microwave lasagna
directions: Crumble beef into a microwave safe colander; place colander in a 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with wax paper; microwave at High 5 to 6 minutes or until meat is no longer pink, stirring after 3 minutes.
Combine beef, sauce, water and wine.
Spread 1/3 of mixture in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange 4 lasagna noodles on sauce.
Layer 1 cup cottage cheese and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese over noodles.
Spoon 1/2 of remaining sauce over cheese.
Repeat process again.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Cover with plastic wrap, folding back one corner for steam to escape. Microwave at Medium 32 to 35 minutes, give dish half-turn after 15 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese and microwave for 2 minutes.
Yields 6 large servings.

title: saucy cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, egg and salt; shape into 50 meatballs. Place in a shallow baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake until browned; turn once.
Spoon off fat.

title: old-fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add Wesson oil, then gradually add flour and buttermilk, alternating flour with milk.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Melt oleo in milk and cool. Beat eggs and add to yeast, then add milk and oleo. Add dry ingredients gradually and place in greased bowl. Cover tightly and refrigerate. When ready to cook, pinch off in biscuit size pieces. Pat out and put on greased pan.
Cook at 350° to 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Will keep in icebox for 4 to 5 days. Do not wait for them to raise.

title: quick cobbler crust
directions: Combine flour, sugar and milk.
Add butter and egg.
Mix well! Pour over top of desired fruit that has been placed in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain fat.
Add Prego and simmer.
Cook noodles as directed.
Layer noodles, sauce and cheese.
Finish with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chilled spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Serves 6.

title: greek cabbage soup
directions: Saute
the
onion in the oil 5 minutes.
Add the water; bring to
a
boil.
Mix
in
the
tomatoes, cabbage, salt and pepper. Bring
to
a
boil again and cook over low heat 1 1/4 hours, or until cabbage is tender.
Taste for seasoning.
Stir in
the parsley.
Serve with sauteed bread.
Beef bone or ham bone
or chunks
may be added for richer taste.
Also soup is very
good if served with melted Gruyere or Mozzarella cheese on top with toasted croutons.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add almond extract.
Stir in flour and baking powder. Mix until smooth.
Turn mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spoon pie filling onto batter in 16 spots.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden and cake tests done.
Filling will sink into cake while baking.
Blueberry filling may be used.

title: cheesy squash custard casserole
directions: Heat oil and butter in large skillet.
Add squash, onion and garlic and saute until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Combine beaten eggs, cheeses, dill, salt and pepper.
Transfer vegetables to buttered 8-inch square baking dish.
Pour egg mixture over.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Cream together margarine or shortening and sugars.
Add eggs. Mix in dry ingredients, then cereals and chocolate chips or raisins. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: casserole of chicken
directions: Blend mayonnaise and water.
Add remaining ingredients except noodles and eggs.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with sliced eggs and Chinese noodles.

title: wild rice and prawn salad(serves 8)
directions: Make rice according to directions; set aside.

title: fried okra
directions: Season okra with salt and cayenne pepper to taste.
Combine flour and cornmeal and season with more salt and cayenne pepper. Dip okra into egg batter and then into flour and cornmeal mixture.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind the cranberries and let stand overnight.
Add sugar. Before serving, add celery, marshmallows and pecans and mix.
Fold in the whipping cream and serve.

title: ice cream sundae dessert
directions: Crush cookies between 2 layers of wax paper to about 1/4 inch size.
Mix with melted margarine. Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
Slice ice cream and spread over the cookie crust. Freeze hard.

title: sausage cornbread bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brown sausage with onion and drain. Combine meal, eggs, corn, milk and oil.
Pour half of mixture into large iron skillet or greased oblong pan.
Sprinkle sausage mixture and cheese over batter.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: holiday orange-blueberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs.
Add butter, orange juice, milk and orange rind.
Mix well.
Pour liquid mixture into dry ingredients and stir only until well moistened.
Carefully fold in nuts and blueberries.
Pour into 5 x 9-inch buttered and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 60 minutes or until toothpick stuck in center comes out clean.
Let set 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Cool on rack.
Wrap and refrigerate overnight before slicing.

title: chicken-fried round steak
directions: Pound the steak thoroughly and cut into serving pieces.
Mix eggs and milk.
Dip meat into egg mixture, then into cracker crumbs.
Handle carefully so all the coating stays on the meat. Heat the fat in a large skillet.
Brown meat on both sides in the hot fat.
Cover tightly and cook over very low heat for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: beef macaroni skillet
directions: Brown beef and onion in 12-inch skillet.
Add tomato juice, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, salt, pepper, mustard and macaroni. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Stir occasionally during cooking.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Butter sides and bottom of glass baking dish.
Combine all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: minestrone soup with ground beef
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven or saucepot over high heat, cook ground beef, onion, celery and cabbage, stirring carefully so that meat stays in chunks, until all pan juices evaporate and meat and vegetables are lightly browned (about 10 minutes).
Add tomatoes, garbanzo beans and corn with all their liquid, zucchini, macaroni, bouillon, basil leaves and water.
Over high heat, heat to boiling, stirring to break up tomatoes.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes, until macaroni and vegetables are tender.

title: sauteed zucchini with raisins
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise and cut into slices about 1/2-inch thick.
In a large frying pan, heat 1 tablespoon of the oil and 1 tablespoon of butter over medium-high heat.
Add half the zucchini and brown on both sides.
Add the remaining oil and butter; saute the rest of the zucchini.
Remove with slotted spoon.

title: meal-in-one soup
directions: Cut meat into small pieces.
Add onion, celery, salt, pepper and a little water.
Cook until tender.
Take meat out of liquid and let cool.
Remove any bones.
To the liquid, add vegetables, barley, tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Put meat back into liquid and cook on simmer until vegetables and barley are tender.
Add water as needed.
Cook and drain macaroni noodles and add to soup while simmering.

title: bev's lemon ice cream pie
directions: Mix together with mixer until fluffy.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust and freeze.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Put water
and
gelatin in saucepan.
Place over direct heat and stir
until dissolved or mixture is clear.
In medium size bowl, combine
condensed
milk
and lemon juice.
Stir in gelatin mixture.
Fold
in
sour
cream.
Mix in 1 1/4 cups of the pie filling.
Turn
into crust.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours. Garnish pie top with remaining chilled pie filling.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper in casserole dish.
Stir in green beans and 1/2 can of French fried onions.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.
Stir and add the rest of onions on top.
Cook 5 more minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in large bowl.
Add milk and margarine. Do not stir.
Microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir just until creamy. Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Stir until blended.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: super dooper chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, oil, both sugars, egg and vanilla together. Add all dry ingredients to oil/sugar mixture.
Mix well. Drop from teaspoon 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Do not overbake!
Remove immediately from cookie sheet.

title: basic chicken bog
directions: Discard liver, gizzard and innards if desired.
Boil chicken in a large covered pot until done, about 1 1/2 hours, with a sprinkling of celery salt and/or garlic powder if you like.
Pour off chicken liquid (broth) and measure.
Cool chicken slightly; strip of bones and skin.
Measure 1 part rice for 2 parts broth, i.e., if you have 4 cups of broth, measure 2 cups rice.
Cut up sausage into 1/2-inch chunks.
Replace chicken, rice, broth and sausage into pot and cover.
Bring everything to a boil, then reduce heat to low.
Don't lift lid for 30 minutes at least, then check to see if rice is done.
If not, continue simmering until rice is done.
Ask anyone for other variations!

title: punch - no ice needed
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in 1/2 gallon of boiling water. Cool.
Add lemon juice, pineapple juice and 2 gallons of water. Freeze overnight.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: christmas wreath
directions: Melt oleo and marshmallows together; when hot, add green food coloring.
Pour over corn flakes.
Mix well.
Spoon into a plate in a wreath design and decorate with red hots.
(Can put a candle in center.)

title: sopaipillas
directions: Combine or mix tortilla flour with warm water.
Slowly swift until it becomes a dough (not too sticky).
Make round balls, then roll out into any shape no bigger than the size of an interior coffee cup.
Preheat pan with vegetable oil, low to medium heat. Lay dough inside pan.
Cook until one side is brown, then flip over and cook the other side until brown.
Combine sugar and cinnamon on another plate; mix with fork.
When tortilla is cooked, place on top of sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle both sides of tortilla well; remove.
Ready to eat.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt oleo.
Cook celery, onions and bell pepper slowly for 40 minutes or until done.
Add seasoned crawfish tails and cook slowly for 40 minutes.
Add parsley with crawfish tails.
Add green onions during the last 10 minutes.
Add cornstarch to thicken just before adding green onions.
Add lemon juice.
Let set for a few minutes. Serve over cooked rice.
May use shrimp.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Place margarine, sugar, milk and cocoa in a saucepan and bring to a hard boil.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter, vanilla, salt and flour.
Stir until well blended.
Press in pan smoothly.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.
You may add chopped peanuts, if desired.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: Sweat the onion in butter until tender.
Add the garlic and sweat briefly.
Add the flour, making a roux, stirring constantly for 5 minutes, until it's golden.
Add the beer and let simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add the cheese and let it melt in.
Add the cream and let the soup continue to warm, just to a simmer.
Do not let it boil.
Add the julienne peppers.
Add the dry mustard, Tabasco and Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Add salt and white pepper to taste.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple honey refresher
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into ice filled glasses. Serves 6.

title: creole grillades
directions: Cut meat in bite-size pieces.
Brown in butter.
Season with salt, pepper and Accent.
Remove.

title: homemade italian spaghetti(special seasoning)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in food processor.
Freeze fatback prior to grinding.
After all ingredients are ground up, add a dash of allspice and basil leaves.
Makes about 6 quarts.

title: oven pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 450° for metal 9 x 13 x 2 baking pan (reduce heat 25° for glass pan). Melt butter in pan in oven until butter is bubbling. Mix remaining ingredients together and pour into hot butter. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Serve immediately with syrup, jam, powdered sugar, etc. for breakfast.

title: butterscotch fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9-inch square pan on sides and bottom.
Melt margarine.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Pour boiling water over oats, sugar and salt.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and add to oats mixture.
Beat in flour; knead until smooth.
Let double in bulk. Shape in 2 loaves and place in greased pans.
Let double again. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Brush tops with butter or margarine.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together shortening, sugar, eggs, water and vanilla until creamy.
Combine flour, salt and soda.
Add to mixture.
Add raisins and oats.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen. 15 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli and onion.
Place in large bowl.
Add shredded cheese, bacon bits, salad dressing, sugar and vinegar.
Stir together.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and green pepper.
Pour salt on top; let sit 1 hour.
Rinse well.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over cucumbers.
Place in jars or large bowl; store in refrigerator.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening with mixer. Add egg. Cream again. Mash bananas and add. Cream. Mix slowly while adding oatmeal. Combine flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg. Fold into creamed ingredients. Add pecans. Spoon onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown. Cool completely. Store in tight container to keep moist.

title: yellow bread
directions: Beat all ingredients, except 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon, for 8 minutes at high speed.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and the cinnamon.
Layer batter and sugar-cinnamon mixture in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Mix together refried beans, green chilies and taco seasoning mix.
Spread on a 12 inch round platter. Blend avocados, lemon juice and 1/2 c. taco sauce until smooth. Spread on top of bean mixture.
Spread sour cream on top of avocado mixture.
Top with shredded lettuce, cheese, taco sauce and olive slices.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: homemade play dough
directions: Cook flour, salt, cream of tartar and oil over medium heat until it thickens.
Add food coloring and knead when cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: chili
directions: Brown the ground beef with diced onion.
Drain off fat.
Put all ingredients in pot.
Bring to a boil and then simmer 1 hour.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place ingredients in a large bowl in the order listed. Mix mayonnaise and sugar thoroughly and place on top of pea layer. Spread it on like frosting. Sprinkle the cheese on top. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: buttermilk fruit salad
directions: Mix buttermilk and pudding mix until smooth.
Add fruit and fold in Cool Whip.
Makes a huge salad.
Half of recipe is enough for a family.

title: marinated fish kabobs
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Cut fish into 1-inch pieces.
To make marinade:
combine oil, soy sauce, scallions, garlic, brown sugar, dried mustard and black pepper.
Place fish pieces in marinade. Cover and let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
